1
00:00:01,301 --> 00:00:04,770
[ Birds Twittering ]

2
00:00:28,394 --> 00:00:31,096
[ Twittering Continues ]

3
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:23,148
[ People Conversing,
 Indistinct ]

4
00:01:25,585 --> 00:01:28,653
[ Children Laughing,
Chattering ]

5
00:01:37,864 --> 00:01:40,932
[ Chattering Continues ]

6
00:01:48,107 --> 00:01:51,076
HURRY UP !
HEY, WAIT !
WAIT FOR ME !

7
00:01:51,078 --> 00:01:53,178
[ Continues Shouting ]

8
00:01:56,883 --> 00:01:58,917
HURRY !

9
00:02:31,751 --> 00:02:34,119
[ Insect Buzzing ]

10
00:02:44,464 --> 00:02:46,531
[ Meows ]

11
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:52,504
[ Woman Screaming ]
NO !  AAH !

12
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:05,150
[ Woman Weeping ]

13
00:03:10,122 --> 00:03:13,158
[ Baby Crying ]

14
00:03:21,501 --> 00:03:24,169
[ Crying Continues ]

15
00:03:37,783 --> 00:03:39,784
YOUR DAUGHTER, SIR.

16
00:03:39,786 --> 00:03:42,854
[ Crying ]

17
00:03:46,158 --> 00:03:48,126
[ Murmuring ]

18
00:03:48,128 --> 00:03:50,195
[ Crying Stops ]

19
00:04:06,312 --> 00:04:09,681
YOU'LL BE WITH
OUR SON IN HEAVEN.

20
00:04:09,683 --> 00:04:12,317
[ Sobbing ]

21
00:04:40,112 --> 00:04:42,113
GOOD AFTERNOON.
GOOD DAY TO YOU,
DOCTOR.

22
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:44,149
FATHER'S HOME !
FATHER'S HOME !

23
00:04:44,151 --> 00:04:46,918
CATHERINE,
QUIETLY, PLEASE.
FATHER !

24
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:50,622
FATHER !
CATHERINE.

25
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:53,825
[ Grunts, Chuckles ]

26
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:58,897
I SEE YOUR INSTRUCTION OF
BEHAVIOR BEFITTING A YOUNG LADY
GOES ON, BUSINESS AS USUAL.

27
00:04:58,899 --> 00:05:01,933
OH, PLEASE DON'T BE ANGRY
WITH AUNT LAVINIA, FATHER.

28
00:05:01,935 --> 00:05:05,003
SHE TRIED TO STOP ME,
BUT MY HEART BEAT MY BREAST...

29
00:05:05,005 --> 00:05:07,172
WITH SUCH
A VOLUPTUOUS SWELL.

30
00:05:07,174 --> 00:05:10,075
TO HAVE A DAUGHTER
WITH SUCH HIGHBROW TASTE...

31
00:05:10,077 --> 00:05:13,778
IN DRESS AND LITERATURE,
AND AT SUCH A YOUNG AGE, WELL.

32
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:16,081
AND IT IS YOU I HAVE TO THANK,
DEAR SISTER.

33
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:17,882
COME, FATHER.
YES, YES.

34
00:05:31,631 --> 00:05:33,665
HERE YOU GO.

35
00:05:43,309 --> 00:05:46,144
[ Choking ]
OH, FATHER,
I'M SO SORRY.

36
00:05:46,146 --> 00:05:49,247
IT WAS A RASPBERRY.
ON THE CONTINENT, PEOPLE PUT--
WE'RE IN NEW YORK.

37
00:05:49,249 --> 00:05:51,316
AND IN NEW YORK,
PORT IS UNADORNED.

38
00:05:51,318 --> 00:05:55,787
IS IT TOO MUCH TO ASK
THAT THERE BE ONE THING
NOT OVERDONE IN THIS HOUSEHOLD ?

39
00:05:55,789 --> 00:05:58,056
- [ Choking ]
- SURPRISE !

40
00:05:58,058 --> 00:06:01,226
[ Together ]
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DR. AUSTIN.
SURPRISE.

41
00:06:01,228 --> 00:06:03,895
[ Party Chattering ]
[ Choking Continues ]

42
00:06:03,897 --> 00:06:07,832
EXCUSE ME, I--
[ Clears Throat ]

43
00:06:07,834 --> 00:06:11,269
MY WINE WENT--
WENT DOWN THE WRONG WAY.

44
00:06:11,271 --> 00:06:13,171
[ Woman ]
COME ALONG, DEAR.
THAT SHOULD BE LOVELY.

45
00:06:13,173 --> 00:06:15,407
[ Chattering Continues ]

46
00:06:15,409 --> 00:06:18,810
NOW DON'T BE NERVOUS.
WE'VE REHEARSED THIS
A THOUSAND TIMES.

47
00:06:19,445 --> 00:06:21,846
SHH, PLEASE.
SIT DOWN.

48
00:06:21,848 --> 00:06:23,882
SWEETHEART ?

49
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,950
[ Chattering Stops ]

50
00:06:29,021 --> 00:06:32,090
* [ Piano ]

51
00:06:38,030 --> 00:06:40,165
* THERE--
[ Clears Throat ]

52
00:06:40,167 --> 00:06:44,269
-  [ Off-Key ]
 * THERE--
- [ Whispering ]

53
00:06:44,271 --> 00:06:46,438
[ Whispering ]
NOW COME ON.

54
00:06:49,241 --> 00:06:53,178
* [ Piano ]

55
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:55,213
[ Off-Key ]
* THERE--

56
00:06:55,215 --> 00:06:57,849
[ Whimpers ]
[ Trickling Sound ]

57
00:06:57,851 --> 00:07:00,952
[ Whispering, Giggling ]

58
00:07:05,324 --> 00:07:07,992
[ Giggling Continues ]

59
00:07:09,195 --> 00:07:13,298
OH, AUSTIN.
SIT DOWN.
COME WITH ME.

60
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:15,200
SHH !  SHH !

61
00:07:15,202 --> 00:07:19,337
MAUREEN !  MAUREEN, THERE'S BEEN
AN ACCIDENT.  DO SOMETHING.

62
00:07:19,339 --> 00:07:22,841
ALICE, WOULD YOU LIKE
TO RECITE SOMETHING FOR US ?

63
00:07:28,347 --> 00:07:30,381
DO YOU WANT YOUR CAKE ?

64
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:46,264
GOOD NIGHT, CATHERINE.
GOOD NIGHT.

65
00:07:52,071 --> 00:07:55,006
GOOD BIRD.  GOOD BIRD.

66
00:08:01,881 --> 00:08:04,883
[ Man, Children
 Chattering ]

67
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:15,560
AH, GOOD AFTERNOON,
DOCTOR.
GOOD AFTERNOON.

68
00:08:15,562 --> 00:08:18,363
FATHER'S HOME !
FATHER'S HOME !

69
00:08:18,365 --> 00:08:20,331
CATHERINE, UNLIKE
THE FOURTH OF JULY,

70
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:23,334
THE OCCASION
OF YOUR FATHER COMING HOME
IS AN EVERYDAY OCCURRENCE.

71
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:28,239
PLEASE DO NOT JANGLE
MY NERVES SO ARBITRARILY.
CATHERINE !

72
00:08:28,241 --> 00:08:30,275
[ Stomping ]
CATHERINE !

73
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:34,345
GOOD AFTERNOON,
DR. SLOPER.

74
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:36,414
GOOD AFTERNOON, FATHER.

75
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:41,352
[ Panting ]
DID YOU FORGET THE PARTY
AT AUNT ELIZABETH'S ?

76
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:44,088
MY DEAR CHILD, THE WORLD
WAS CREATED IN SIX DAYS.

77
00:08:44,090 --> 00:08:48,526
SURELY WE MORTALS CAN PREPARE
FOR A GATHERING IN THREE HOURS.
[ Laughing ]

78
00:08:54,099 --> 00:08:58,903
FATHER, THERE IS
SO MUCH TO DO.

79
00:09:07,112 --> 00:09:09,280
PLEASE, I BEG YOU,
ALLOW ME TO ATTEND MYSELF.

80
00:09:09,282 --> 00:09:12,350
I FEAR WHAT WILL HAPPEN
IF I KEEP YOU FROM YOUR
PREPARATIONS A MOMENT LONGER.

81
00:09:12,352 --> 00:09:14,419
[ Laughing ]

82
00:09:17,323 --> 00:09:19,324
CATHERINE !

83
00:09:39,545 --> 00:09:41,546
[ Door Opens ]

84
00:09:41,548 --> 00:09:45,383
HOW LONG COULD IT TAKE FOR ONE
WOMAN TO MINISTER TO HERSELF ?

85
00:09:45,385 --> 00:09:48,620
NOW, AUSTIN, CHOOSING ONE'S
FIRST EVENING GOWN ALONE...

86
00:09:48,622 --> 00:09:51,055
IS A GREAT EVENT
FOR A YOUNG GIRL.

87
00:09:51,057 --> 00:09:54,259
PLEASE... BE GENTLE.

88
00:09:54,261 --> 00:09:58,196
IF A PRELUDE IS NECESSARY,
IT MUST BE BAD INDEED.

89
00:10:10,509 --> 00:10:14,212
SO THIS MAGNIFICENT CREATURE
IS MY CHILD.

90
00:10:14,214 --> 00:10:17,282
I'LL GO CHANGE.
YOU'VE TAKEN UP
ENOUGH TIME ALREADY.

91
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:20,585
COME ALONG.

92
00:10:36,468 --> 00:10:38,569
YAH !  YAH !

93
00:10:50,082 --> 00:10:53,084
GOOD DAY,
MRS. THORNBRED.
GOOD DAY.

94
00:10:55,688 --> 00:10:59,123
OH, IT'S UNCLE AUSTIN.
UNCLE AUSTIN.
[ Chattering ]

95
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:02,694
[ Girls ]
UNCLE AUSTIN !  UNCLE AUSTIN !

96
00:11:02,696 --> 00:11:04,562
LAVINIA.
OH.

97
00:11:04,564 --> 00:11:08,499
OH, ELIZABETH.
HELLO,
AUNT LAVINIA.

98
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:10,501
WHAT A HAVEN OF PEACE
AND TRANQUILITY.

99
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:13,504
OH, DEAR BROTHER,
THAT'S A SURE SIGN
OF GETTING OLD.

100
00:11:13,506 --> 00:11:17,442
IT DOES SEEM THAT
THE YOUNG GET MORE RAUCOUS
AS WE GET OLDER.

101
00:11:17,444 --> 00:11:19,477
IT'S DELIGHTFUL.

102
00:11:19,479 --> 00:11:24,315
ANYTHING SHORT OF HIS OWN CHAIR
IN HIS FRONT ROOM
SEEMS VIOLENT TO AUSTIN.

103
00:11:24,317 --> 00:11:27,986
LAVINIA HAS NOT
COTTONED ONTO THE FACT
THAT SHE'S A SHEEP.

104
00:11:27,988 --> 00:11:30,655
* [ Men Singing ]

105
00:11:30,657 --> 00:11:34,225
LOVELY, DEAR.
OH, I DON'T THINK
FATHER APPROVES.

106
00:11:34,227 --> 00:11:36,394
WELL, DON'T LET THAT
TROUBLE YOU UNDULY, MY DEAR.

107
00:11:36,396 --> 00:11:39,464
IF THERE'S ONE THING
I'VE LEARNED OF MY BROTHER
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,

108
00:11:39,466 --> 00:11:43,301
IT'S THAT HE'S GENERALLY
NOT THE APPROVING SORT.

109
00:11:43,303 --> 00:11:46,604
COME.  MARIAN IS
EAGER TO SEE YOU.

110
00:11:46,606 --> 00:11:49,374
* THERE THEY ARE
THERE THEY ARE
THERE THEY ARE *

111
00:11:49,376 --> 00:11:52,443
* [ Continues ]

112
00:11:53,779 --> 00:11:56,047
OH, SEE HOW
SHE BEAMS ?

113
00:11:56,049 --> 00:11:59,384
THEY MUST BE
VERY MUCH IN LOVE.
DEAR CHILD, HE'S A STOCKBROKER.

114
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:01,285
HE'LL MAKE A FINE HUSBAND.

115
00:12:01,287 --> 00:12:03,421
THAT IS ALL
MARRYING REQUIRES.

116
00:12:03,423 --> 00:12:06,724
I OFTENTIMES THINK
IT'S EASIER TO BE BASIC.

117
00:12:06,726 --> 00:12:10,461
ONE'S NEEDS
ARE SO SIMPLE.
A POLKA !

118
00:12:10,463 --> 00:12:13,197
WHY DO THEY DO THAT TO ME ?
MARIAN,
CATHERINE'S HERE.

119
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:15,733
CATHERINE.
A NEW DRESS ?

120
00:12:15,735 --> 00:12:18,236
[ All Chattering
 Simultaneously ]

121
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:21,139
ONE MUST TAKE CARE
OF OTHER'S NEEDS
BEFORE ONE'S OWN.

122
00:12:21,141 --> 00:12:23,374
CAN YOU IMAGINE ANYTHING
MORE DISAGREEABLE ?

123
00:12:23,376 --> 00:12:25,810
[ Elizabeth ]
CONGRATULATIONS, MY DEAR.
MAY I ?

124
00:12:25,812 --> 00:12:28,246
[ Chattering Continues ]

125
00:12:32,484 --> 00:12:35,686
IF I WANTED TO BE A PIONEER,
I'D SETTLE IN MINNESOTA.
ISN'T SHE PRETTY ?

126
00:12:35,688 --> 00:12:38,189
I THINK IT'S BEASTLY
WE CAN'T DANCE.
I KNOW.

127
00:12:38,191 --> 00:12:40,358
[ Man ]
SO WE'LL BUY A NEW HOUSE
EVERY THREE OR FOUR YEARS.

128
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:43,561
WE'LL KEEP MOVING UP.
IS IT TRUE IT'S
ALL THE RAGE IN PARIS ?

129
00:12:43,563 --> 00:12:47,732
-  MORRIS.  MORRIS.
- WHAT IS IT YOU WANT ME
  TO DO NOW MARIAN ?

130
00:12:47,734 --> 00:12:49,667
YOU MUST TAKE CATHERINE
OUTSIDE TO DANCE.

131
00:12:49,669 --> 00:12:53,471
IF YOUR WIFE-TO-BE IS THIS
DEMANDING OF ME, DEAR COUSIN,
CAN YOU IMAGINE--

132
00:12:53,473 --> 00:12:55,473
[ Man ]
OH, YES, I CAN.

133
00:12:55,475 --> 00:12:58,342
SOMEONE HAS TO DEMAND OF YOU.
IT MAY HELP TO BUILD
SOME LONG-AWAITED CHARACTER.

134
00:12:58,344 --> 00:13:01,479
YOU SEE WHAT YOU'VE DONE ?
YOU'VE MADE POOR MISS--

135
00:13:03,749 --> 00:13:05,850
MISS--

136
00:13:05,852 --> 00:13:08,119
MISS--

137
00:13:11,423 --> 00:13:14,192
[ Giggling ]
ANSWER HIM, PLEASE.

138
00:13:14,194 --> 00:13:17,395
HE'S CONCEITED ENOUGH
TO BELIEVE HE HAS
MADE YOU SPEECHLESS.

139
00:13:17,397 --> 00:13:21,265
THIS IS CATHERINE SLOPER,
MARIAN'S COUSIN.
THIS IS MORRIS TOWNSEND.

140
00:13:24,703 --> 00:13:28,339
SHALL WE ?
COME.

141
00:13:28,341 --> 00:13:31,476
* [ Chamber Orchestra ]

142
00:13:37,349 --> 00:13:40,418
[ Laughing, Chattering ]

143
00:14:01,273 --> 00:14:04,308
ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX.

144
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:06,911
ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX.

145
00:14:06,913 --> 00:14:12,450
IF I CAN HAVE YOUR ATTENTION
UP HERE, I PROMISE YOU
I'LL TAKE CARE OF DOWN THERE.

146
00:14:12,452 --> 00:14:15,253
[ Both Grunting ]

147
00:14:15,255 --> 00:14:18,222
OH, FORGIVE ME.
I'VE BEEN OFF THE DANCE FLOOR
FOR FAR TOO LONG, IT SEEMS.

148
00:14:18,224 --> 00:14:21,559
HERE. LET'S TRY
THIS DANGEROUS SPORT.

149
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:27,298
HERE.

150
00:14:29,601 --> 00:14:31,636
PLEASE SIT DOWN.
OH.

151
00:14:32,738 --> 00:14:35,540
I'LL GET SOME
REFRESHMENTS, SHALL I ?
OH.

152
00:14:35,542 --> 00:14:38,609
* [ Continues ]

153
00:14:52,324 --> 00:14:54,358
OH, GRACIOUS.

154
00:14:57,729 --> 00:15:00,565
- MY DEAR, WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
HIDING IN THE BUSHES ?
- NO--

155
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:03,534
YOU MUST COME OUT WHERE
THE YOUNG MEN CAN SEE YOU--
NO, NO, NO.

156
00:15:09,274 --> 00:15:11,409
OH, MY.

157
00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:14,979
I D-- I DON'T BELIEVE
WE'VE BEEN INTRODUCED.
MORRIS TOWNSEND.

158
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:18,849
COUSIN TO ARTHUR.  I BEGGED
MISS SLOPER TO TAKE PITY ON ME.

159
00:15:18,851 --> 00:15:22,386
I'M AFRAID, AS A DANCER,
I MAKE A VERY GOOD HORSEMAN.

160
00:15:22,388 --> 00:15:25,790
WELL, MR. TOWNSEND, I CAME
LOOKING FOR MY NIECE...

161
00:15:25,792 --> 00:15:29,293
BECAUSE THERE WERE
SEVERAL YOUNG MEN
SEARCHING FOR HER FRANTICALLY.

162
00:15:29,295 --> 00:15:33,331
SHE'S BEEN IGNORING
HER DANCE CARD SHAMELESSLY.

163
00:15:33,333 --> 00:15:36,867
HOWEVER, IF SHE'S PROMISED
TO KEEP YOU COMPANY,

164
00:15:36,869 --> 00:15:39,437
I'LL TRY TO KEEP THEM
AT BAY A LITTLE LONGER.

165
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:43,474
NOW, I'VE MET THE MOST CHARMING
WOMEN HERE TONIGHT, BUT THEY
ALL COME FROM THE SAME FAMILY.

166
00:15:43,476 --> 00:15:46,544
IT'S REMARKABLE.
[ Gasping ]

167
00:15:46,546 --> 00:15:49,847
I'M GOING TO PRETEND
I DIDN'T FIND YOU, CATHERINE.

168
00:15:49,849 --> 00:15:53,551
BUT YOU MUST NOT MONOPOLIZE HER,
MR. TOWNSEND.
OH, NO.

169
00:15:54,987 --> 00:15:58,823
WELL, I SEE OUR TIME IS LIMITED.
I MUST MAKE THE MOST OF IT.

170
00:15:58,825 --> 00:16:02,360
I DON'T WANT TO EARN
THE ENMITY OF EVERY MAN HERE.

171
00:16:02,362 --> 00:16:05,830
PLEASE DON'T MOCK ME,
MR. TOWNSEND.

172
00:16:05,832 --> 00:16:07,832
I'VE OFFENDED YOU.

173
00:16:07,834 --> 00:16:10,301
NO.  NO, I--

174
00:16:11,303 --> 00:16:14,005
MR. ROBBINS.  HE'S--

175
00:16:14,007 --> 00:16:16,641
HE'S--

176
00:16:16,643 --> 00:16:20,645
DO YOU SEE ?
AND, UH, MR. ALMOND.

177
00:16:22,748 --> 00:16:25,850
HE'S-- HE'S MY--

178
00:16:25,852 --> 00:16:29,320
[ Laughing ]
HE'S MY UNCLE.

179
00:16:30,622 --> 00:16:35,026
A WOMAN WITHOUT GUILE.
WHAT A RARITY.

180
00:16:35,028 --> 00:16:38,596
[ Laughing ]
GUILE ?  ME ?
NO.

181
00:16:38,598 --> 00:16:42,400
I MEAN, A WOMAN
OF SUCH UNCOMMON GRACE HAS--
HAS NO NEED OF GUILE.

182
00:16:44,936 --> 00:16:47,071
PLEASE DON'T BANISH ME.

183
00:16:47,073 --> 00:16:50,308
YOU SEE, I'VE BEEN AWAY
FOR A VERY LONG TIME.

184
00:16:50,310 --> 00:16:53,511
AND IF YOU LEAVE ME, I-- I'LL
BE FORCED TO MAKE MY OWN WAY...

185
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:57,915
IN-- IN THIS STRANGE AND
I'M QUITE SURE DANGEROUS WORLD.

186
00:16:59,785 --> 00:17:02,320
I KNEW
I HADN'T BEEN MISTAKEN.

187
00:17:02,322 --> 00:17:06,490
YOU ARE INDEED GRACIOUS--
FAR BEYOND WHAT I DESERVE,
I'M SURE.

188
00:17:06,492 --> 00:17:09,427
YOU ARE SO BEAUTIFUL, I--

189
00:17:10,095 --> 00:17:13,431
[ Laughing ]
OH, THANK YOU.

190
00:17:13,433 --> 00:17:15,599
[ Moans ]
OH, ALLOW ME.

191
00:17:17,402 --> 00:17:20,004
[ Sighs ]
MISS SLOPER.
MISS--

192
00:17:22,942 --> 00:17:27,678
- WHO'S THAT YOUNG FOREIGNER
TALKING TO CATHERINE ?
-  THAT'S NO FOREIGNER.

193
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:30,414
BUT YOU'RE RIGHT
IN THINKING HIM ONE.

194
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:33,718
- HE LOOKS QUITE BRILLIANT.
-  HE'S ARTHUR'S COUSIN, AUSTIN.

195
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:37,421
SEVERAL TIMES REMOVED,
OF COURSE.
OF COURSE.

196
00:17:37,423 --> 00:17:39,790
YOU SEE, THERE ARE TOWNSENDS,
AND THEN THERE ARE TOWNSENDS.

197
00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:43,594
THE YOUNG BRANCHES,
ELDER BRANCHES, OF COURSE.
INFERIOR BRANCHES ?

198
00:17:43,596 --> 00:17:45,763
WELL, THAT'S THE WAY IT IS
WITH ALL ROYAL LINES.

199
00:17:45,765 --> 00:17:47,732
[ Marian ]
ARTHUR.
EXCUSE ME.

200
00:17:47,734 --> 00:17:50,401
YOUR MOTHER
WANTS TO SEE US BOTH.

201
00:17:50,403 --> 00:17:53,471
AUSTIN, YOU MUST
CHOOSE YOUR OPPONENTS
WITH MORE DISCRETION.

202
00:17:53,473 --> 00:17:55,473
UH, GO FIND
ALICE, GIRLS.

203
00:17:55,475 --> 00:17:58,442
OTHERWISE, THERE'S
NO SPORT TO SLAUGHTER.

204
00:17:58,444 --> 00:18:01,512
* [ Violin ]

205
00:18:12,791 --> 00:18:14,759
THANK YOU.

206
00:18:14,761 --> 00:18:16,861
GOOD-BYE, MY DEAR.

207
00:18:18,563 --> 00:18:20,731
MISS SLOPER,

208
00:18:20,733 --> 00:18:23,167
YOU DROPPED THIS.

209
00:18:55,967 --> 00:18:59,003
[ Austin ]
THAT CHARMING YOUNG MAN
WAS UNCOMMONLY TENDER,

210
00:18:59,005 --> 00:19:01,038
LAVINIA,
WHENEVER YOU CONVERSED.

211
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:03,908
HE HAD
SUCH A DEVOTED AIR.

212
00:19:03,910 --> 00:19:06,577
MY DEAR BROTHER,
THE DEVOTION WAS NOT TO ME.

213
00:19:06,579 --> 00:19:09,180
IT WAS OF CATHERINE
HE SPOKE.

214
00:19:09,182 --> 00:19:13,017
SO HE'S IN LOVE WITH
THIS REGAL CREATURE, THEN ?
OH, FATHER !

215
00:19:13,019 --> 00:19:16,921
HE DIDN'T SAY THAT.
BUT HE ADMIRED HER DRESS.

216
00:19:16,923 --> 00:19:21,459
IT MUST BE LOVE, OR HE THINKS
SHE HAS 80,000 A YEAR.

217
00:19:21,461 --> 00:19:25,696
I DON'T BELIEVE HE THINKS
OF THAT.  HE'S TOO REFINED.

218
00:19:25,698 --> 00:19:28,933
HE MUST BE
TREMENDOUSLY REFINED.
YES.

219
00:19:28,935 --> 00:19:32,203
YES, HE--  YES.

220
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:51,655
MISS SLOPER--
[ Surprised Shout ]

221
00:19:51,657 --> 00:19:53,691
OH !
I'M SORRY.  I'M--

222
00:19:56,161 --> 00:19:59,196
I'M SO SORRY.
YOUR MUSIC.

223
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:01,232
[ Sighs ]

224
00:20:02,934 --> 00:20:06,504
[ Chuckles ]
MY-- MY CLUMSINESS IN YOUR
PRESENCE IS BECOMING LEGENDARY.

225
00:20:09,207 --> 00:20:11,275
EX-- EXCUSE ME.

226
00:20:13,144 --> 00:20:15,145
I'M SORRY
TO HAVE BOTHERED YOU.

227
00:20:15,147 --> 00:20:18,649
YEAH, I WAS-- I WAS JUST
SO HAPPY TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

228
00:20:18,651 --> 00:20:20,818
AND I-- I'M SORRY.

229
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:23,687
YOU KNOW, I DON'T
ALWAYS KNOW HOW TO--

230
00:20:23,689 --> 00:20:25,923
PLEASE ACCEPT
MY APOLOGIES.

231
00:20:25,925 --> 00:20:27,925
MR. TOWNSEND--
OH !

232
00:20:27,927 --> 00:20:29,894
SORRY.

233
00:20:29,896 --> 00:20:31,996
OH, MY !

234
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:53,751
YOU'RE SO BLESSED
TO HAVE A TALENT FOR MUSIC.

235
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:55,786
OH, I HAVE NO TALENT.

236
00:20:55,788 --> 00:20:59,990
JUST, UM, APPRECIATION.
YEARNING.

237
00:20:59,992 --> 00:21:02,760
OH, CAN IT BE
THAT I HAVE FOUND A TWIN ?

238
00:21:02,762 --> 00:21:05,729
YOU-- YOU SEE, MUSIC IS SUCH
AN INTENSE LOVE OF MINE...

239
00:21:05,731 --> 00:21:09,833
THAT MY WEAKNESS
IN THE EXECUTION OF IT IS
THE CAUSE OF GREAT PAIN...

240
00:21:09,835 --> 00:21:12,937
AND, AT TIMES,
GREATER EMBARRASSMENT.

241
00:21:12,939 --> 00:21:16,607
Y-- YOU SEE, I REFUSE
TO ACCEPT THAT I AM SO
UNTALENTED AT SOMETHING...

242
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:18,776
THAT TOUCHES ME
SO DEEPLY,

243
00:21:18,778 --> 00:21:21,011
I-- I SIMPLY BELIEVE
THAT I'VE NOT YET...

244
00:21:21,013 --> 00:21:24,214
DISCOVERED THE KEY
THAT WILL UNLOCK THE GIFT.

245
00:21:24,216 --> 00:21:26,250
I KNOW.
REALLY ?

246
00:21:26,252 --> 00:21:30,854
YES.  THAT--
THAT'S THE EXACT THING.

247
00:21:30,856 --> 00:21:34,892
EVERY NIGHT I INCLUDE
A MENTION OF IT IN MY PRAYERS.
[ Laughs ]

248
00:21:34,894 --> 00:21:37,328
I THOUGHT
THAT I WAS ALONE.

249
00:21:37,330 --> 00:21:39,296
OH.

250
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:42,166
DO YOU SUPPOSE
IT'S POSSIBLE THAT WE COULD--

251
00:21:44,002 --> 00:21:48,005
I-- I LIVE WITH MY SISTER
AND-- AND HER FIVE CHILDREN
WHILE I SEEK EMPLOYMENT.

252
00:21:48,007 --> 00:21:50,307
AND OUR SITUATION
DOESN'T ALLOW...

253
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:53,677
FOR SUCH FRIVOLITY
AS MUSICAL INSTRUMENTS.

254
00:21:53,679 --> 00:21:57,114
BUT DO YOU SUPPOSE THAT IT WOULD
EVER BE POSSIBLE THAT WE COULD--

255
00:21:58,049 --> 00:22:02,353
YOU ARE BRAVE.
I AM NOT, SO MUCH.

256
00:22:02,355 --> 00:22:06,323
I SO WANT TO FIND FAVOR
WITH YOU.  PLEASE--
[ Gasps ]

257
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:10,327
PLEASE-- PLEASE DON'T BELIEVE
THAT I AM SO MUCH A FOOL
AS I APPEAR WITH YOU.

258
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:13,797
I CAN'T SEEM--
I CAN'T SEEM TO--

259
00:22:13,799 --> 00:22:15,833
HERE'S ANOTHER.

260
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:20,037
GOOD DAY.

261
00:22:21,039 --> 00:22:23,340
MR. TOWNSEND ?
[ Clears Throat ]

262
00:22:24,776 --> 00:22:28,345
WE WOULD BE PLEASED TO EXTEND
THE USE OF OUR PIANO.

263
00:22:38,189 --> 00:22:40,190
IS TOMORROW TOO SOON...

264
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:44,728
FOR OUR SLOPER-TOWNSEND
MUSIC SOCIETY TO COMMENCE ?

265
00:22:44,730 --> 00:22:47,164
NO.  NOT--
NOT TOO SOON.  YES.

266
00:23:21,266 --> 00:23:24,334
* [ Piano ]

267
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:28,806
* [ Continues ]

268
00:23:41,152 --> 00:23:43,220
[ Whispers, Indistinct ]

269
00:23:43,222 --> 00:23:45,255
[ Whispering ]
YOUR AUNT IS LEAVING.

270
00:23:46,257 --> 00:23:49,226
YOU'LL HAVE TO EXCUSE ME,
MR. TOWNSEND.

271
00:23:49,228 --> 00:23:51,328
I HAVE THE MOST
FORTUITOUS HEADACHE.

272
00:23:51,330 --> 00:23:53,330
OF COURSE.

273
00:23:53,332 --> 00:23:55,365
EXCUSE ME.

274
00:23:55,367 --> 00:23:57,968
AUNT ?
HMM ?

275
00:23:57,970 --> 00:24:01,438
I CAN HARDLY BE AN AUDIENCE
TO YOU AND MR. TOWNSEND FOREVER.

276
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:05,109
I'VE NEGLECTED MY DUTIES
SHAMELESSLY THESE PAST WEEKS.

277
00:24:05,111 --> 00:24:09,113
BESIDES, MOST YOUNG LADIES CRAVE
TIME ALONE WITH THEIR BEAUX.

278
00:24:09,115 --> 00:24:11,115
HE IS NOT MY BEAU.

279
00:24:11,117 --> 00:24:14,118
MR. TOWNSEND'S INTEREST
IS IN THE PIANO.

280
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:17,121
ACCOMPLISHED AS MR. TOWNSEND
MAY BE IN MANY AREAS,

281
00:24:17,123 --> 00:24:19,123
HE'S NO FREDERIC CHOPIN.

282
00:24:19,125 --> 00:24:22,359
AND EVEN MR. CHOPIN WOULD BE
HARD-PRESSED TO TRAVEL...

283
00:24:22,361 --> 00:24:26,063
FIVE TIMES A WEEK FOR FOUR WEEKS
ACROSS TOWN IN AN OMNIBUS...

284
00:24:26,065 --> 00:24:29,099
TO PRACTICE ON AN INSTRUMENT
SO IN NEED OF TUNING.

285
00:24:29,101 --> 00:24:32,536
BESIDES, I HAVE
THE YOUNG MAN'S CONFIDENCE.

286
00:24:32,538 --> 00:24:34,505
HE'S COME A-COURTING.

287
00:24:34,507 --> 00:24:38,041
[ Giggles ]
TAKE MR. BYRON'S ADVICE:

288
00:24:38,043 --> 00:24:40,144
"BE WARM, BUT PURE.

289
00:24:40,146 --> 00:24:42,446
BE AMOROUS, BUT BE CHASTE."

290
00:24:42,448 --> 00:24:44,515
NO, NO !
GO.  GO.

291
00:24:57,328 --> 00:25:00,330
ARE YOU AFRAID
TO BE ALONE WITH ME ?
HMM ?

292
00:25:01,533 --> 00:25:03,867
MM, MM, NO.

293
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:08,038
JUST DOES NOT SEEM
QUITE PROPER.

294
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:12,242
IS PROPER
SO IMPORTANT TO YOU ?

295
00:25:17,949 --> 00:25:20,951
IS A STROLL
IN THE PARK PROPER ?

296
00:25:22,053 --> 00:25:24,121
WILL THAT
MAKE YOU HAPPY ?

297
00:25:27,292 --> 00:25:31,028
YOU KNOW,
I ASK FOR NOTHING MORE.

298
00:25:31,030 --> 00:25:33,096
EH, WE-- YOU DO.

299
00:25:38,336 --> 00:25:41,205
[ Chattering ]

300
00:25:41,207 --> 00:25:43,607
GOOD AFTERNOON,
DOCTOR.
GOOD AFTERNOON.

301
00:25:44,576 --> 00:25:46,610
HOW DO YOU DO ?

302
00:25:49,214 --> 00:25:51,215
AFTERNOON.
LOVELY DAY, DOCTOR.

303
00:25:57,889 --> 00:26:00,257
THEY'RE RATHER HUMBLE,
I'M AFRAID.

304
00:26:00,259 --> 00:26:02,292
[ Catherine ]
NO, THEY'RE LOVELY.

305
00:26:02,294 --> 00:26:05,562
OH, BUT THEY PALE
IN COMPARISON TO YOU.
[ Laughing ]

306
00:26:07,365 --> 00:26:09,266
[ Laughs ]

307
00:26:14,572 --> 00:26:17,407
MAUREEN SAID YOU WANTED
TO SEE ME, AUSTIN ?

308
00:26:18,610 --> 00:26:22,379
WOULD YOU CARE
FOR SOME PORT ?
OH, MY.
[ Laughs ]

309
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:42,165
THERE.

310
00:26:43,902 --> 00:26:46,270
THIS IS MY FAVORITE
TIME OF DAY,

311
00:26:46,272 --> 00:26:48,305
WATCHING THE SUN GO DOWN...

312
00:26:48,307 --> 00:26:52,976
AS THE CITY WINDS TO A CLOSE,
SO PEACEFUL AND QUIET.

313
00:26:52,978 --> 00:26:54,945
IT QUITE LULLS ONE...

314
00:26:54,947 --> 00:26:58,348
INTO A SENSE
OF RESTFUL TRANQUILITY.

315
00:26:58,350 --> 00:27:03,387
[ Laughs ]
ABSOLUTELY FALSE, AS IT HAPPENS,
BECAUSE DARKNESS IS FALLING,

316
00:27:03,389 --> 00:27:07,090
AND MY DAUGHTER IS RUNNING WILD
IN A PUBLIC PARK WITH A MAN;

317
00:27:07,092 --> 00:27:10,360
A VIRTUAL STRANGER TO ME, BUT
BY ALL APPEARANCES NOT TO HER.

318
00:27:10,362 --> 00:27:13,297
OH, AUSTIN--
ARE YOUR DUTIES
TOO NUMEROUS, LAVINIA ?

319
00:27:13,299 --> 00:27:16,199
LET US TAKE THEIR NUMBER,
SHALL WE ?

320
00:27:16,201 --> 00:27:20,504
WELL, THERE'S, UH,
CHAPERONING CATHERINE.

321
00:27:20,506 --> 00:27:23,607
AND THERE'S, UH--

322
00:27:23,609 --> 00:27:25,642
WE-WELL, THAT'S IT.

323
00:27:25,644 --> 00:27:29,579
SHOULD I PERHAPS
HIRE YOU AN ASSISTANT ?

324
00:27:29,581 --> 00:27:32,282
I-- I WOULDN'T WANT
TO TAKE ADVANTAGE...

325
00:27:32,284 --> 00:27:35,218
OF OUR FAMILIAL BOND
BY OVERWORKING YOU.

326
00:27:38,456 --> 00:27:41,491
[ Door Opens ]
[ Catherine Stomping ]

327
00:27:42,527 --> 00:27:45,262
OH, FATHER, ISN'T THAT
A BEAUTIFUL DAY ?

328
00:27:48,299 --> 00:27:51,301
PERHAPS IT'S TIME
I MADE THE ACQUAINTANCE
OF YOUR YOUNG MAN.

329
00:27:51,303 --> 00:27:53,303
YES !
[ Lavinia Chuckles ]

330
00:27:56,374 --> 00:28:01,278
SO IN SHORT, I WOULD SAY
THAT IF A GONDOLA DOESN'T COME
EQUIPPED WITH A GONDOLIER,

331
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:04,414
WALKING IS A VERY GOOD PLAN,
UNLESS, OF COURSE,
YOU LIKE TO SWIM.

332
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:07,217
[ All Laughing ]

333
00:28:07,219 --> 00:28:09,653
OH, MORRIS, MORRIS,
TELL-- TELL DR. SLOPER...

334
00:28:09,655 --> 00:28:12,723
ABOUT THE TIME IN SWITZERLAND
WHEN YOU TOOK IT INTO YOUR HEAD
TO SCALE THE ALPS.

335
00:28:12,725 --> 00:28:18,996
I'M SURE THE TELLING WOULD
BENEFIT FROM A GOOD CIGAR AND,
UH, SOME EXCELLENT PORT WINE.

336
00:28:18,998 --> 00:28:20,998
WHAT DO YOU THINK,
MR. TOWNSEND ?

337
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:23,667
OH, I-- I THINK A STORY
CAN'T HELP BUT BE IMPROVED
BY SUCH ACCOUTREMENTS.

338
00:28:23,669 --> 00:28:27,738
SINCE YOU BOTH KNOW THE STORY,
IT CAN'T BE THAT MUCH
OF AN INCONVENIENCE.  SHALL WE ?

339
00:28:27,740 --> 00:28:30,240
YES, OF COURSE.
EXCUSE ME.

340
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:46,356
[ Whispering ]
AUNT.  NO, NO.
[ Men Murmuring ]

341
00:28:47,625 --> 00:28:49,659
[ Silently ]

342
00:28:51,696 --> 00:28:55,365
I'M SURE YOU HAVE ANY NUMBER
OF DELIGHTFUL STORIES
THAT WOMEN ARE ENTHRALLED WITH.

343
00:28:55,367 --> 00:28:59,403
NOW IT IS YOU WHO ARE
BEING KIND.  [ Chuckles ]
[ Chuckles ]

344
00:28:59,405 --> 00:29:01,772
THERE.
THANK YOU.

345
00:29:01,774 --> 00:29:04,708
I HEAR YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR A POSITION.

346
00:29:04,710 --> 00:29:08,178
WHAT ARE YOU FIT FOR ?
NOT VERY MUCH,
I'M AFRAID.

347
00:29:08,180 --> 00:29:11,815
I HAVE ONLY A GOOD RIGHT ARM,
AS THEY SAY IN MELODRAMAS.

348
00:29:11,817 --> 00:29:18,755
IN ADDITION TO YOUR GOOD RIGHT
ARM, YOU HAVE YOUR SUBTLE BRAIN
AND AMAZING PHYSIOGNOMY.

349
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:22,726
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO ANSWER IN THE FACE
OF SUCH GENEROUS OBSERVATION.

350
00:29:22,728 --> 00:29:25,395
YOU ADVISE ME, THEN,
NOT TO DESPAIR ?

351
00:29:25,397 --> 00:29:28,432
I SHOULD BE SORRY TO ADMIT
THAT ANY ROBUST,

352
00:29:28,434 --> 00:29:31,334
WELL-DISPOSED YOUNG MAN
NEED EVER DESPAIR.

353
00:29:32,637 --> 00:29:36,840
WERE YOU KINDLY INTENDING
TO PROPOSE SOMETHING
TO MY ADVANTAGE ?

354
00:29:36,842 --> 00:29:40,377
IT OCCURS TO ME
I SOMETIMES HEAR OF POSITIONS
OUTSIDE OF NEW YORK.

355
00:29:40,379 --> 00:29:43,480
MM.  I'M AFRAID
I COULDN'T MANAGE THAT.

356
00:29:43,482 --> 00:29:45,782
YOU SEE, I'M-- I'M MY SISTER'S
ONLY LIVING RELATIVE.

357
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:50,253
SHE'S A WIDOW,
AND I'M PROVIDING AN EDUCATION
FOR HER FIVE CHILDREN.

358
00:29:50,255 --> 00:29:54,257
I AM SURE YOU MUST BE
A GREAT COMFORT TO HER
IN THE CIRCUMSTANCES.

359
00:29:54,259 --> 00:29:58,528
AS, UH, HONORABLE AS THAT IS,
IT IS HARDLY A CAREER.

360
00:29:58,530 --> 00:30:01,331
MM.  IT WILL NOT
MAKE MY FORTUNE,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU MEAN.

361
00:30:01,333 --> 00:30:03,633
ARE YOU BENT
ON MAKING A FORTUNE ?

362
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:07,704
ON THE CONTRARY, I'M SIMPLY
LOOKING TO TURN AN HONEST PENNY.

363
00:30:07,706 --> 00:30:09,840
I SHALL KEEP THAT IN MIND.

364
00:30:09,842 --> 00:30:14,277
IF MY SITUATION BECOMES
DESPERATE, I SHALL PERHAPS TAKE
THE LIBERTY OF REMINDING YOU.

365
00:30:14,279 --> 00:30:17,314
BE ASSURED, I WILL NOT
LOSE SIGHT OF YOU.

366
00:30:17,316 --> 00:30:20,484
NOW, I'M-- I'M QUITE IN THE MOOD
OF AN ALPINE ADVENTURE.

367
00:30:20,486 --> 00:30:25,422
AND LEAVE OUT NONE
OF THE DETAILS THAT I'M SURE
YOU DID FOR THE LADIES.

368
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:31,361
[ Men Laughing ]

369
00:30:31,363 --> 00:30:34,431
WHAT CAN THEY BE TALKING ABOUT,
ALL THIS TIME ?

370
00:30:38,569 --> 00:30:41,404
I FEEL ONE OF MY HEADACHES
COMING ON.

371
00:30:41,406 --> 00:30:45,242
IF YOU WISH TO RETIRE,
I WILL MAKE YOUR EXCUSES.
[ Door Opens ]

372
00:30:45,244 --> 00:30:47,677
OH.
[ Whispering ]
DID IT GO WELL ?

373
00:30:51,916 --> 00:30:55,152
HE'S AN EXTRAORDINARY MAN,
YOUR FATHER.

374
00:30:55,154 --> 00:30:57,154
HE'S THE TYPE OF MAN
I WOULD WISH TO BE.

375
00:30:57,156 --> 00:31:00,657
I KNEW
YOU TWO WOULD GET ALONG.

376
00:31:00,659 --> 00:31:03,426
AND WHAT IF WE HADN'T ?

377
00:31:03,428 --> 00:31:07,264
I SHOULD LIKE YOU TO TELL ME
THAT IT WOULDN'T HAVE MATTERED.

378
00:31:07,266 --> 00:31:11,468
BUT OF COURSE
IT WOULD HAVE MATTERED.
IT WOULD HAVE MATTERED GREATLY.

379
00:31:13,337 --> 00:31:16,406
YOU WOULD NOT HAVE WELCOMED
THE OPPORTUNITY
TO CONTRADICT HIM.

380
00:31:18,242 --> 00:31:20,277
I NEVER CONTRADICT HIM.

381
00:31:20,279 --> 00:31:23,380
YOU WOULD HEAR ME ABUSED
WITHOUT OPENING YOUR LIPS
IN MY DEFENSE ?

382
00:31:23,382 --> 00:31:28,351
MY FATHER WOULD NOT ABUSE YOU.
HE DOES NOT KNOW YOU
WELL ENOUGH.

383
00:31:28,353 --> 00:31:30,453
[ Both Laughing ]

384
00:31:30,455 --> 00:31:34,691
I'D LIKE US TO PLAY
FOR YOUR FATHER, CATHERINE.
NO.

385
00:31:34,693 --> 00:31:38,795
DON'T YOU KNOW YET THAT
TOGETHER WE HAVE SANCTUARY ?

386
00:31:40,464 --> 00:31:42,799
COME.  COME.

387
00:31:44,835 --> 00:31:46,903
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

388
00:32:01,452 --> 00:32:04,321
* [ Piano ]

389
00:32:09,227 --> 00:32:11,294
[ Murmuring ]

390
00:32:20,404 --> 00:32:23,440
* [ Italian ]

391
00:32:43,694 --> 00:32:47,497
* [ Continues ]

392
00:33:32,576 --> 00:33:35,645
* [ Joins In ]

393
00:34:14,785 --> 00:34:17,454
* [ Ends ]

394
00:34:23,694 --> 00:34:26,363
BRAVO.

395
00:34:33,070 --> 00:34:36,773
HE THAT WILL NOT
APPLY NEW REMEDIES
MUST EXPECT NEW EVILS.

396
00:34:40,911 --> 00:34:43,980
[ Women Giggling ]

397
00:34:47,017 --> 00:34:49,052
[ Whispers ]
WOULD YOU GO ?
[ Shrieks ]

398
00:34:53,057 --> 00:34:55,058
[ Door Closes ]

399
00:35:28,159 --> 00:35:31,161
CATHERINE, I'M--

400
00:35:31,163 --> 00:35:34,431
FORGIVE ME, I'M TREMBLING
LIKE A SCHOOLBOY.

401
00:35:38,135 --> 00:35:41,104
I NEVER IMAGINED
I'D BE TAKEN LIKE THIS.

402
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:45,175
I MUST-- I MUST CONFESS
I ACQUIRED A CERTAIN...

403
00:35:45,177 --> 00:35:48,745
VENEER DURING MY TRAVELS.

404
00:35:48,747 --> 00:35:51,080
BUT, UM, I'D HEARD TALES
OF THIS-- THIS THING,

405
00:35:51,082 --> 00:35:53,883
BUT I SUSPECTED
IT WAS AN IDEA...

406
00:35:53,885 --> 00:35:56,586
ORIGINATED BY
MERCENARY NOVELISTS.

407
00:35:58,122 --> 00:36:00,790
YOU KNOW,
I FIND MYSELF--

408
00:36:00,792 --> 00:36:05,028
I FIND MYSELF PERFORMING
THE MOST USELESS TASKS...

409
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:09,032
IN THE HOPE THAT I'LL FIND
A MOMENT'S RESPITE
FROM THINKING OF YOU.

410
00:36:13,037 --> 00:36:15,238
I-- I'M QUITE OVERCOME.

411
00:36:34,625 --> 00:36:37,660
[ Chattering,
Applauding ]

412
00:36:45,202 --> 00:36:47,704
OH, MISS, MISS.

413
00:36:47,706 --> 00:36:50,106
LET ME HELP YOU.

414
00:36:52,276 --> 00:36:55,512
[ Bell Jingling ]

415
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:06,523
OH, YOU MUST BE
MORE CAREFUL, DEAR.

416
00:37:08,158 --> 00:37:10,894
ON THIS MOST HAPPY
OF OCCASIONS,

417
00:37:10,896 --> 00:37:14,597
I WOULD LIKE TO CONGRATULATE
MY DAUGHTER AND MY SON-IN-LAW.

418
00:37:16,166 --> 00:37:19,302
-  MY GREATEST HOPE FOR YOU BOTH
IS THAT YOUR YEARS TOGETHER...
- MADAM ?  SIR ?

419
00:37:19,304 --> 00:37:22,205
- THANK YOU.
-  WILL BE AS HAPPY AND
 AS BOUNTIFUL...

420
00:37:22,207 --> 00:37:24,207
AS YOUR MOTHER'S
AND MINE HAVE BEEN.

421
00:37:24,209 --> 00:37:27,243
[ Man ]
WELL SAID.  WONDERFUL.
ABSOLUTELY WONDERFUL.

422
00:37:32,716 --> 00:37:34,817
I'LL DO MY BEST
FOR HER.

423
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:41,991
[ Arthur ]
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

424
00:37:46,697 --> 00:37:49,666
THREE CHEERS.
LOVE AND PROSPERITY.
TO THE COUPLE.

425
00:37:49,668 --> 00:37:52,235
HEAR, HEAR.

426
00:37:52,237 --> 00:37:55,271
AUSTIN, DON'T YOU THINK
HE'S CHARMING ?

427
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:58,241
SO YOU TOO BELIEVE
THAT HE'S PAYING ATTENTION
TO MY DAUGHTER...

428
00:37:58,243 --> 00:38:00,843
FOR HER UNCOMMON BEAUTY
AND WIT.

429
00:38:00,845 --> 00:38:03,913
WOULD THIS BE AN INOPPORTUNE
TIME TO REMIND YOU...

430
00:38:03,915 --> 00:38:07,317
WAS VERY WELL ENDOWED MONETARILY
WHEN YOU HAD OCCASION
TO MARRY HER ?

431
00:38:07,319 --> 00:38:11,220
- YOU'RE CERTAINLY NOT
SUGGESTING, ARE YOU--
- I SUGGEST NOTHING.

432
00:38:11,222 --> 00:38:14,157
FOR YOU NOR MR. TOWNSEND.

433
00:38:14,159 --> 00:38:16,793
I MERELY STATE FACTS.

434
00:38:16,795 --> 00:38:19,729
HE'S ALTOGETHER TOO FAMILIAR,
TOO SELF-ASSURED.  HE'S--

435
00:38:19,731 --> 00:38:23,266
RAVISHING, POSSESSED OF
A RAPIER WIT AND A VELVET CHARM.

436
00:38:23,268 --> 00:38:26,369
WHILE YOU, DEAR AUSTIN--
[ Groans ]

437
00:38:28,706 --> 00:38:32,308
NOW, IF YOU ARE REALLY INTENT
ON GATHERING INSIDE INFORMATION,

438
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:35,311
MRS. MONTGOMERY,
THE MUCH-MENTIONED SISTER.

439
00:38:36,647 --> 00:38:38,648
[ Girl ]
CATHERINE, DO YOU WANT
TO PLAY WITH US ?

440
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:40,683
YES, YES, COME ALONG !

441
00:38:40,685 --> 00:38:45,288
CATHERINE, WAIT.  MARTHA,
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET CATHERINE.

442
00:38:45,290 --> 00:38:48,858
MY DEAR CATHERINE,
I AM SO PLEASED TO MEET YOU.
[ Giggles ]

443
00:38:48,860 --> 00:38:51,661
MORRIS HAS TOLD ME
SO MUCH ABOUT YOU.
MARTHA--

444
00:38:53,664 --> 00:38:55,665
I AM CATHERINE.

445
00:38:55,667 --> 00:38:58,901
I HAVE HEARD
MUCH ABOUT YOU TOO.

446
00:38:58,903 --> 00:39:01,304
MAY I PRESENT
ALICE ALMOND, MY COUSIN ?

447
00:39:01,306 --> 00:39:03,773
HOW DO YOU DO ?
[ Bell Jingling ]

448
00:39:03,775 --> 00:39:07,844
OH, CATHERINE, LOOK.
WE'RE MISSING THE RING.  COME.
WILL YOU EXCUSE US ?

449
00:39:07,846 --> 00:39:10,947
[ Jingling Continues ]

450
00:39:11,982 --> 00:39:14,283
- I'M--
- THANK YOU, MARTHA.

451
00:39:15,719 --> 00:39:18,721
YES.
[ Laughing ]

452
00:39:18,723 --> 00:39:22,291
OH, THAT'S A LARGE PIECE.
WATCH THE GLASS.

453
00:39:22,293 --> 00:39:24,327
[ Arthur ]
WELL, I'M A BROKER,
NOT A WAITER.

454
00:39:24,329 --> 00:39:26,329
[ Marian ]
OH, HERE, HERE.  I'M SORRY, I--
[ Arthur ]  THANK YOU.

455
00:39:26,331 --> 00:39:28,231
I HOPE THERE'S ENOUGH.

456
00:39:28,233 --> 00:39:30,433
[ Girl ]
FOR ALICE.
OKAY, ALICE.

457
00:39:30,435 --> 00:39:34,971
[ Marian ]  HERE WE GO.
[ Arthur ]
WHO'S GOING TO FIND THE RING ?

458
00:39:34,973 --> 00:39:38,808
-  [ Marian ]  ANYONE ?
-  [ Woman ]  YOURS IS ON
 THE BRINK OF PROPOSING !

459
00:39:38,810 --> 00:39:41,978
KEEP LOOKING.
I MET THIS--

460
00:39:41,980 --> 00:39:44,213
WHO'S NEXT ?
THANK YOU.

461
00:39:44,215 --> 00:39:47,283
[ Marian ]
CAROLINE.  CAROLINE.
[ Squealing ]

462
00:39:47,285 --> 00:39:51,187
OH !
IT'S CATHERINE,
IS IT ?

463
00:39:51,189 --> 00:39:53,256
[ Applause ]

464
00:39:57,227 --> 00:39:59,862
* [ Chamber Orchestra ]

465
00:39:59,864 --> 00:40:02,932
[ Applause Continues ]

466
00:40:05,235 --> 00:40:07,403
INTRODUCE ME.

467
00:40:13,444 --> 00:40:16,345
[ Elizabeth ]
MAY I PRESENT MY BROTHER,
DR. SLOPER ?

468
00:40:16,347 --> 00:40:19,348
[ Marian ]
OH, MY BROTHER--

469
00:40:22,119 --> 00:40:24,187
MISS PENNIMAN,
Y-- YOUR HANDKERCHIEF.

470
00:40:24,189 --> 00:40:28,191
BEWARE THE IDES OF MARCH.
WE MUST MEET AND PLAN.
DANGER IS AT HAND.

471
00:40:52,950 --> 00:40:55,918
HERE YOU ARE.
WHERE DID THAT COME FROM ?

472
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:57,954
THE CAKE.
YOU CAUGHT
THE RING IN THE CAKE ?

473
00:40:59,223 --> 00:41:02,325
WELL, I HOPE
THAT'S A GOOD OMEN.

474
00:41:04,294 --> 00:41:07,029
YOUR FATHER
IS INVESTIGATING ME.

475
00:41:12,236 --> 00:41:14,937
HE DOESN'T TRUST ME,
I'M AFRAID.

476
00:41:14,939 --> 00:41:17,840
I DON'T SEE HOW
YOU COULD KNOW.

477
00:41:17,842 --> 00:41:20,109
I FEEL IT.

478
00:41:20,111 --> 00:41:22,145
I'M VERY QUICK TO FEEL.

479
00:41:24,114 --> 00:41:26,983
MORRIS.

480
00:41:26,985 --> 00:41:29,852
WHEN MY MOTHER
AND MY BROTHER WERE TAKEN,

481
00:41:29,854 --> 00:41:31,888
I BECAME FATHER'S LIFE.

482
00:41:33,056 --> 00:41:35,892
[ Sighs ]
HE MUST FEEL...

483
00:41:35,894 --> 00:41:39,996
CERTAIN THAT HE HAS DONE
HIS DUTY TOWARDS ME.

484
00:41:39,998 --> 00:41:44,200
IF I WERE BEING
PURSUED BY THE POPE,
HE WOULD INVESTIGATE HIM TOO.

485
00:41:44,202 --> 00:41:49,272
IF YOU WERE BEING PURSUED
BY THE POPE, HE SHOULD INDEED
HAVE CAUSE FOR DISMAY.

486
00:41:50,841 --> 00:41:53,409
[ Laughing ]

487
00:41:53,411 --> 00:41:55,511
[ Laughs ]

488
00:41:57,347 --> 00:41:59,916
IT'S MY SIZE.

489
00:41:59,918 --> 00:42:02,285
[ Whispering ]
I LOVE YOU.

490
00:42:02,287 --> 00:42:04,320
I LOVE YOU.

491
00:42:05,522 --> 00:42:08,324
[ Chuckles ]

492
00:42:08,326 --> 00:42:11,060
HOW CHARMING.

493
00:42:11,062 --> 00:42:14,197
YOU'VE, UH, TRAVELED
EXTENSIVELY, MRS. MONTGOMERY ?

494
00:42:14,199 --> 00:42:16,432
[ Laughing ]
OH, MY BROTHER.

495
00:42:16,434 --> 00:42:19,402
HE'S COLLECTED SOMETHING
FROM EVERYWHERE HE'S EVER BEEN
FOR ME.

496
00:42:19,404 --> 00:42:22,305
ARE YOU CLOSE TO HIM ?
OH, YES.

497
00:42:22,307 --> 00:42:24,574
WE WERE ORPHANED FROM AN
EARLY AGE AND REARED EACH OTHER.

498
00:42:26,176 --> 00:42:28,878
WHAT SORT OF GENTLEMAN
IS YOUR BROTHER ?

499
00:42:28,880 --> 00:42:31,514
[ Grunting ]
EXCUSE ME.

500
00:42:31,516 --> 00:42:33,549
THANK YOU, THERESE.

501
00:42:37,588 --> 00:42:40,590
IT'S DIFFICULT TO TALK
ABOUT ONE'S BROTHER.

502
00:42:40,592 --> 00:42:43,960
IT SEEMS TO ME IT IS NOT
WHEN ONE HAS GOOD THINGS TO SAY.

503
00:42:43,962 --> 00:42:48,331
OH, YES, EVEN THEN, WHEN SUCH
A GREAT DEAL DEPENDS UPON IT.

504
00:42:48,333 --> 00:42:51,067
AND FOR YOUR BROTHER,
A GREAT DEAL DOES DEPEND ON IT.

505
00:42:51,069 --> 00:42:54,337
I MEANT FOR MISS SLOPER.

506
00:42:54,339 --> 00:42:56,906
PLEASE SIT DOWN.
OH, THANK YOU.

507
00:43:05,315 --> 00:43:08,351
- WHAT DOES HE TELL YOU ?
- THAT HE IS IN LOVE.

508
00:43:08,353 --> 00:43:13,089
YOU CAN'T BE THAT OBTUSE.
IT'S MY BELIEF YOUR BROTHER
LIVES OFF YOU.

509
00:43:13,091 --> 00:43:17,326
NOW HE MEANS TO LIVE OFF
MY POOR CATHERINE, AND SHE'S
TOO SIMPLEMINDED TO SEE IT.

510
00:43:20,397 --> 00:43:24,467
IF THAT IS TRULY
WHAT YOU BELIEVE,
THEN YOUR PATH IS A SIMPLE ONE:

511
00:43:24,469 --> 00:43:27,136
DON'T LET HER MARRY HIM.

512
00:43:27,138 --> 00:43:29,572
YOU HAVE DAUGHTERS ?
YES.

513
00:43:29,574 --> 00:43:33,910
WHEN YOUNG MEN COME A-COURTING,
YOU WILL BE CONCERNED
WITH THEIR MORAL CHARACTER.

514
00:43:33,912 --> 00:43:36,245
CATHERINE IS ILL-EQUIPPED
TO LOOK AFTER HERSELF.

515
00:43:36,247 --> 00:43:40,383
I CAN'T STAND BY AND SEE HER
MAKE SO GREAT A MISTAKE.

516
00:43:40,385 --> 00:43:45,388
IF I'D THROW HIM BACK ON YOU,
THE LEAST I CAN DO
IS HELP WITH THE BURDEN.

517
00:43:45,390 --> 00:43:47,990
I SHALL TAKE THE LIBERTY
OF PLACING IN YOUR HANDS...

518
00:43:47,992 --> 00:43:50,326
AN AMOUNT
FOR YOUR BROTHER'S SUPPORT.

519
00:43:50,328 --> 00:43:53,362
NO WONDER YOU HAVE SUCH
A GREAT CONCERN ABOUT MONEY.

520
00:43:53,364 --> 00:43:56,399
YOU BELIEVE
IT CAN BUY ANYTHING.

521
00:43:56,401 --> 00:43:58,100
MAMA !

522
00:43:58,102 --> 00:44:00,269
YOU'LL FORGIVE ME
FOR TELLING YOU:

523
00:44:00,271 --> 00:44:04,340
IT'S EASY TO SAY
WHEN ONE HAS NOT EXPERIENCED
PURCHASING POWER.

524
00:44:04,342 --> 00:44:08,244
PEOPLE TALK GREATLY ABOUT IT:
PLAIN, STUPID GIRL...

525
00:44:08,246 --> 00:44:10,246
WITH A LARGE FORTUNE...

526
00:44:10,248 --> 00:44:13,149
MARRYING A HANDSOME,
WORLDLY MAN WITHOUT A PENNY.

527
00:44:13,151 --> 00:44:16,218
DON'T THEY, DOCTOR ?
IMAGINE THE INDIGNITY.

528
00:44:16,220 --> 00:44:20,089
WHY, PEOPLE MIGHT EVEN THINK
THAT YOU HAD BEEN TAKEN
FOR A FOOL.

529
00:44:20,091 --> 00:44:23,259
IT'S MORE
THAN A MAN IN YOUR POSITION
SHOULD EVER HAVE TO BEAR.

530
00:44:24,561 --> 00:44:27,530
YOU DO ME
A GRAVE INJUSTICE.
DO I ?

531
00:44:27,532 --> 00:44:32,201
TIME WILL TELL THE TRUTH OF IT.
EXCUSE ME.

532
00:45:19,616 --> 00:45:23,119
[ Austin ]
MR. TOWNSEND, I HOPE
YOU WEREN'T WAITING TOO LONG.

533
00:45:23,121 --> 00:45:25,688
YOU CAN ONLY APPROXIMATE
HOW LONG THESE THINGS TAKE.

534
00:45:25,690 --> 00:45:29,258
OH, NO.  IT'S A WONDERFUL THING
TO HAVE A PROFESSION.

535
00:45:29,260 --> 00:45:33,763
AH, BUT IT'S NOT ONLY
A THING ONE HAS.  IT'S A THING
ONE MUST APPLY DAILY.

536
00:45:33,765 --> 00:45:37,466
YES, BUT THERE IS
TREMENDOUS SATISFACTION
IN THAT APPLICATION.

537
00:45:37,468 --> 00:45:41,771
AS MUCH AS IN SCALING AN ALP
OR RIDING IN A GONDOLA ?

538
00:45:41,773 --> 00:45:44,540
WELL, I'M SURE I WOULDN'T KNOW,
NEVER HAVING HAD A PROFESSION.

539
00:45:44,542 --> 00:45:46,809
SO WE'RE AT AN IMPASSE,
AS THEY SAY,

540
00:45:46,811 --> 00:45:51,814
FOR I'VE NEVER SCALED AN ALP
FOR BEING OCCUPIED WITH
APPLYING MY PROFESSION.

541
00:45:51,816 --> 00:45:55,084
I WISH TO MARRY
YOUR DAUGHTER, SIR.

542
00:45:58,789 --> 00:46:02,358
SHE IS SIMPLY
ONE OF THE MOST DELIGHTFUL...

543
00:46:02,360 --> 00:46:05,528
AND CHARMING INDIVIDUALS
I'VE EVER ENCOUNTERED.

544
00:46:05,530 --> 00:46:08,464
MR. TOWNSEND, YOU MUST BE
VERY SUSCEPTIBLE.

545
00:46:08,466 --> 00:46:12,101
AS CATHERINE'S FATHER,
I HAVE, I TRUST, A JUST...

546
00:46:12,103 --> 00:46:15,838
AND TENDER APPRECIATION
OF HER MANY GOOD QUALITIES.

547
00:46:15,840 --> 00:46:19,742
BUT I DON'T MIND TELLING YOU,
I'VE NEVER THOUGHT OF HER
AS DELIGHTFUL OR CHARMING...

548
00:46:19,744 --> 00:46:23,446
AND NEVER EXPECTED
ANYONE ELSE TO EITHER.

549
00:46:23,448 --> 00:46:27,249
WELL, I'M SURE I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'D THINK OF CATHERINE
IF I WERE HER FATHER.

550
00:46:27,251 --> 00:46:31,487
I CAN'T PUT MYSELF
IN THAT PLACE.  I SPEAK
FROM MY OWN POINT OF VIEW.

551
00:46:31,489 --> 00:46:33,522
AND YOU SPEAK VERY WELL.

552
00:46:33,524 --> 00:46:37,093
KEEP TALKING, SIR, FOR
I FEEL SURE YOU'LL BE TELLING ME
NEXT OF HER BEAUTY AND WIT.

553
00:46:37,095 --> 00:46:39,495
DR. SLOPER,
I DON'T PRETEND TO KNOW...

554
00:46:39,497 --> 00:46:43,299
WHAT ALCHEMY
IS AT WORK HERE,

555
00:46:43,301 --> 00:46:47,803
BUT THE FACT IS, I'VE NEVER BEEN
HAPPIER THAN THESE TEN WEEKS.

556
00:46:47,805 --> 00:46:50,840
TO INTRODUCE MAGIC
TO A MAN OF SCIENCE
IN THE COURSE OF A DIALOGUE...

557
00:46:50,842 --> 00:46:55,478
SIGNALS THAT COMMON GROUND
HAS LONG DEPARTED.

558
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:58,647
WELL, THEN-- THEN LET ME SPEAK
A LANGUAGE YOU WILL UNDERSTAND.

559
00:46:58,649 --> 00:47:03,219
I'VE LIVED LONG ENOUGH TO LEARN
CERTAIN TRUTHS ABOUT MYSELF.

560
00:47:03,221 --> 00:47:06,589
ONE IS THAT MY VANITY
REQUIRES AN AUDIENCE.

561
00:47:06,591 --> 00:47:11,160
NOW, THIS IS NOT THE MOST
ATTRACTIVE OF TRAITS, AND WOMEN
ARE QUICK TO ACKNOWLEDGE THIS.

562
00:47:11,162 --> 00:47:13,195
NOT SO, CATHERINE.

563
00:47:13,197 --> 00:47:17,333
I TIRE MYSELF
BEFORE SHE TIRES OF ME,
WHICH IS SAYING A GREAT DEAL.

564
00:47:17,335 --> 00:47:21,403
WHAT YOU SEE,
AND MY STORIES,

565
00:47:21,405 --> 00:47:24,607
ARE ALL I BRING
TO THIS UNION.

566
00:47:24,609 --> 00:47:27,776
AND SHE MAKES ME FEEL
LIKE THE MOST IMPORTANT BEING...

567
00:47:27,778 --> 00:47:30,246
EVER TO ROAM THE PLANET.

568
00:47:30,248 --> 00:47:33,716
DO YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO BE THE MOST IMPORTANT PERSON
IN THE WORLD TO SOMEONE ?

569
00:47:33,718 --> 00:47:37,520
PERHAPS YOU DO.  PERHAPS
THAT IS--  PERHAPS THAT IS WHAT
BRINGS US TO THIS TO THIS PLACE.

570
00:47:37,522 --> 00:47:40,456
CATHERINE IS SO GOOD...

571
00:47:40,458 --> 00:47:44,326
AND HONEST AND-- AND TRUE.

572
00:47:44,328 --> 00:47:49,298
SHE-- SHE LIVES
IN A PLACE WHERE EVERYTHING
IS SHINING AND CLEAN...

573
00:47:49,300 --> 00:47:51,901
AND WHERE EVERYONE HAS
THE BEST OF INTENTIONS.

574
00:47:51,903 --> 00:47:54,603
I NEVER IMAGINED
SUCH A WORLD.

575
00:47:54,605 --> 00:47:58,374
AND NOW I WANT
TO LIVE THERE WITH HER.

576
00:47:58,376 --> 00:48:01,410
YOU ARE
A REMARKABLE INDIVIDUAL.

577
00:48:04,681 --> 00:48:08,817
AS A DINNER COMPANION,
AS A STORYTELLER,
AS A MAN OF THE WORLD...

578
00:48:08,819 --> 00:48:13,789
AND, IN FACT,
AS A SUPERIOR HUMAN BEING,
I TAKE OFF MY HAT TO YOU.

579
00:48:13,791 --> 00:48:17,293
BUT THE ABSENCE
OF EMPLOYMENT, MEANS,

580
00:48:17,295 --> 00:48:20,496
A PROFESSION,
ANY VISIBLE PROSPECTS...

581
00:48:20,498 --> 00:48:23,232
PLACE YOU IN A CATEGORY FROM
WHICH IT WOULD BE IMPRUDENT...

582
00:48:23,234 --> 00:48:26,435
FOR ME TO CHOOSE
A HUSBAND FOR MY DAUGHTER.

583
00:48:29,272 --> 00:48:31,440
BUT-- BUT IT'S NOT
FOR YOU TO CHOOSE.

584
00:48:31,442 --> 00:48:34,577
IT'S FOR CATHERINE TO,
AND SHE HAS CHOSEN ME.
YOU'VE SPENT A LIFE IDLING.

585
00:48:34,579 --> 00:48:37,913
NOW YOU'VE DECIDED IT'S TIME
YOU FOUND A POSITION--

586
00:48:37,915 --> 00:48:42,451
A POSITION IN THE PARLOR
OF 21 WASHINGTON SQUARE AS THE
HUSBAND OF A WEAK-MINDED WOMAN.

587
00:48:42,453 --> 00:48:44,820
YOU SEE, YOU NEED NOT BE
CONCERNED WITH MY EYESIGHT.

588
00:48:44,822 --> 00:48:47,456
BUT THAT IS NOT
WHAT CATHERINE SEES.

589
00:48:47,458 --> 00:48:49,325
I HAVE 26 YEARS...

590
00:48:49,327 --> 00:48:53,629
AND THE DEEP WELL OF HER RESPECT
AND ADMIRATION TO DRAW FROM.

591
00:48:53,631 --> 00:48:55,698
I'LL SUPPLY HER
WITH A PAIR OF SPECTACLES.

592
00:48:55,700 --> 00:48:59,568
WELL, DO NOT FORGET THAT I, TOO,
DRAW FROM THAT SAME WELL.

593
00:48:59,570 --> 00:49:03,472
[ Chortling ]
THIS IS TOO AMUSING.
YOU MEAN TO DEFY ME.

594
00:49:03,474 --> 00:49:09,445
A MAN WHO SPENDS HIS LIFE--
YOU CALL IT IDLING; I CALL IT
SEARCHING-- SEEKS SOMETHING.

595
00:49:09,447 --> 00:49:11,680
FOR ME, IT WAS HAPPINESS.

596
00:49:11,682 --> 00:49:15,851
BY HAVING GONE TO THE ENDS
OF THE EARTH IN PURSUIT OF IT,
WHAT DO YOU SUPPOSE...

597
00:49:15,853 --> 00:49:19,555
ARE THE CHANCES OF GIVING IT UP,
HAVING DISCOVERED IT
ON HIS DOORSTEP ?

598
00:49:19,557 --> 00:49:22,625
PLEASE EXCUSE ME.
I AM LATE FOR LUNCH.

599
00:49:36,473 --> 00:49:38,540
[ Eager Sigh ]

600
00:49:49,986 --> 00:49:51,987
[ Door Closes ]

601
00:49:51,989 --> 00:49:54,056
[ Austin Murmuring ]

602
00:50:38,101 --> 00:50:40,469
[ Women Whispering ]

603
00:50:40,471 --> 00:50:43,672
[ Whispering ]
WOULD YOU JUST GO AWAY ?
OH !

604
00:50:53,650 --> 00:50:57,119
[ Man ]
COME ON, MA'AM.
YOU'VE HAD YOUR LOOK.

605
00:51:02,525 --> 00:51:03,092
HMM.

606
00:51:08,398 --> 00:51:11,633
[ Men Shouting ]
COME ON, DIGS !
NO TIME FOR TAIL WAGGIN' !

607
00:51:11,635 --> 00:51:14,036
-  EASY, BOY !
-  [ Barking ]
- [ Screams ]

608
00:51:18,108 --> 00:51:20,142
WE'LL GO THROUGH THIS WAY.

609
00:51:29,119 --> 00:51:32,154
YOU MAY DISROBE NOW.
OH, MR. TOWNSEND.

610
00:51:32,156 --> 00:51:35,657
I REFUSE TO CARRY ON
A CONVERSATION WITH THAT...
CONTRAPTION.

611
00:51:35,659 --> 00:51:38,093
I HAVE MY REPUTATION
TO THINK OF.

612
00:51:38,095 --> 00:51:42,965
THEN WHY CHOOSE AN
ESTABLISHMENT THAT FAIRLY
REEKS OF LICENTIOUSNESS ?

613
00:51:42,967 --> 00:51:48,470
I'D HEARD IT WAS RELIABLE
FOR THINGS CLANDESTINE.
DO YOU HAVE ANYTHING FOR ME ?

614
00:51:48,472 --> 00:51:52,107
HE WILL NEVER CHANGE.
TO DO SO WOULD BE
TO SURRENDER.

615
00:51:52,109 --> 00:51:56,478
I KNOW HIS HARD,
INTELLECTUAL NATURE.
HE'S IMPERVIOUS TO PITY.

616
00:51:56,480 --> 00:51:59,047
HE WILL BE VANQUISHED ONLY
BY THE ESTABLISHED FACT.

617
00:51:59,049 --> 00:52:01,950
WELL, IT'S A FACT THAT
I WANT TO MARRY HIS DAUGHTER.

618
00:52:01,952 --> 00:52:05,521
I PRESENTED IT TO HIM,
AND HE DIDN'T SEEM
IN THE LEAST VANQUISHED.

619
00:52:05,523 --> 00:52:09,057
MARRY CATHERINE FIRST.
MEET HIM AFTERWARD.

620
00:52:10,427 --> 00:52:13,195
YOU MEAN I SHOULD
CARRY HER OFF ?
ELOPE ?

621
00:52:13,197 --> 00:52:17,032
WELL, DON'T YOU SEE ?
HE THINKS YOU LIKE
THE MONEY.

622
00:52:17,034 --> 00:52:19,668
IF YOU MARRY HER,
KNOWING THAT SHE'LL BE
DISINHERITED,

623
00:52:19,670 --> 00:52:24,206
HE HAS NO CHOICE
BUT TO SEE THAT
YOU'RE HONORABLE.

624
00:52:24,208 --> 00:52:27,810
WOULD YOU REALLY WISH
THE LIFE OF A PAUPER
ON YOUR NIECE ?

625
00:52:27,812 --> 00:52:30,179
SHE HAS 10,000 A YEAR
FROM HER MOTHER.

626
00:52:30,181 --> 00:52:32,481
SHE'S USED TO MORE.

627
00:52:32,483 --> 00:52:37,219
YOU KNOW, MY HUSBAND,
THE GOOD REVEREND,
ONCE MARRIED A YOUNG COUPLE...

628
00:52:37,221 --> 00:52:40,222
IN THE SAME DISTRESS.

629
00:52:40,224 --> 00:52:43,959
THE FATHER WAS RECONCILED
AFTERWARD.  EVERYTHING
WORKED OUT BEAUTIFULLY.

630
00:52:43,961 --> 00:52:48,764
WELL, UNFORTUNATELY, WE DO NOT
HAVE REVEREND PENNIMAN TO MARRY
US.
NO, BUT YOU HAVE ME.

631
00:52:48,766 --> 00:52:54,470
I CAN'T PERFORM THE CEREMONY,
OF COURSE, BUT I CAN
BE IN ATTENDANCE.

632
00:52:54,472 --> 00:52:58,240
WE MUST USE
A SUBTERRANEAN CHAPEL
WITH LITTLE LIGHTING SO--

633
00:52:58,242 --> 00:53:00,843
IS THIS WHAT YOU
CALLED ME HERE TO ASK ME ?

634
00:53:00,845 --> 00:53:06,748
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
WISH TO SEE SOMEONE
CLOSE TO CATHERINE...

635
00:53:06,750 --> 00:53:09,251
TO SEND HER WORD,
A MESSAGE...

636
00:53:09,253 --> 00:53:12,754
A LOCK OF HAIR.

637
00:53:14,224 --> 00:53:18,126
SHE KNOWS MY HEART.
AS I DO.

638
00:53:18,128 --> 00:53:22,130
I KNOW IT TO BE GOOD
AND CONSTANT AND TRUE.

639
00:53:22,132 --> 00:53:26,869
YOU CANNOT KNOW THIS,
BUT I WENT TO GREAT
PERSONAL PERIL TO COME HERE.

640
00:53:29,539 --> 00:53:34,243
AUSTIN THREATENED TO THROW ME
TO THE ELEMENTS AND WORSE
IF I CONTINUED TO HELP YOU.

641
00:53:34,245 --> 00:53:39,214
HOWEVER, I CANNOT SIT BY...
AND SEE YOU IN DISTRESS.

642
00:53:39,216 --> 00:53:42,551
MY NATURE DEMANDS
THAT IF I CAN BE
OF ASSISTANCE...

643
00:53:42,553 --> 00:53:45,587
IN MATTERS OF THE HEART,
I MUST BE.

644
00:53:45,589 --> 00:53:48,524
I'M THINKING ONLY OF YOU,
MORRIS.

645
00:53:48,526 --> 00:53:52,294
I RACKED MY BRAINS
TRYING TO THINK OF WAYS
TO HELP YOU.

646
00:53:52,296 --> 00:53:55,230
I PAY THE PENALTY
WITH MY HEADACHES.

647
00:53:55,232 --> 00:53:58,667
[ Couple Moaning In Ecstasy ]
MY PERFECT CIRCULATE
OF PAIN.

648
00:53:58,669 --> 00:54:02,938
BUT I CARRY IT AS A QUEEN
CARRIES HER CROWN.

649
00:54:02,940 --> 00:54:07,609
-  [ Moaning, Shouting ]
- WHAT ARE THEY DOING IN THERE ?

650
00:54:07,611 --> 00:54:10,746
YOU KNOW,
I HAVE NO IDEA.
[ Gasps ]

651
00:54:10,748 --> 00:54:13,215
OH, MY GOODNESS !

652
00:54:13,217 --> 00:54:15,217
[ Exhales Sharply ]

653
00:54:25,228 --> 00:54:27,329
[ Twittering ]

654
00:54:33,603 --> 00:54:35,604
AH, SWEETS.

655
00:54:35,606 --> 00:54:37,573
PRETTY THING.
PRETTY--

656
00:54:37,575 --> 00:54:39,641
[ Morris ]
CATHERINE !

657
00:55:10,273 --> 00:55:12,341
[ Sighing ]

658
00:55:21,117 --> 00:55:23,185
[ Fire Crackling ]

659
00:55:24,687 --> 00:55:28,290
[ Knocking ]
YES ?

660
00:55:37,100 --> 00:55:39,101
FATHER...

661
00:55:42,238 --> 00:55:46,174
YOU TOLD ME IF I HAD
ANYTHING TO SAY ABOUT
MR. TOWNSEND...

662
00:55:46,176 --> 00:55:50,045
YOU WOULD BE AVAILABLE
TO LISTEN.

663
00:55:50,047 --> 00:55:52,347
I WISH TO SEE HIM.

664
00:55:52,349 --> 00:55:56,318
- TO BID HIM GOOD-BYE.
- HE'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

665
00:56:05,795 --> 00:56:08,864
WOULD YOU LIKE TO MAKE
YOUR FATHER VERY HAPPY ?

666
00:56:10,733 --> 00:56:14,770
IF I CAN.
YOU CAN AND YOU WILL.
IT DEPENDS ON YOUR WILL.

667
00:56:14,772 --> 00:56:17,205
IS IT TO GIVE HIM UP ?

668
00:56:21,077 --> 00:56:25,213
YOU ARE HAPPIER THAN I.
I HAVE NO DOUBT
YOU'RE UNHAPPY NOW.

669
00:56:25,215 --> 00:56:30,452
BUT IT'S BETTER TO BE UNHAPPY
FOR THREE MONTHS AND GET OVER IT
THAN BE UNHAPPY FOREVER.

670
00:56:30,454 --> 00:56:36,224
BUT THE ONLY THING THAT
WOULD MAKE ME UNHAPPY FOREVER
WOULD BE TO BE WITHOUT HIM.

671
00:56:36,226 --> 00:56:41,930
YOU SUPPOSE I KNOW
NOTHING OF MEN ?
THEIR VICES AND FALSITIES ?

672
00:56:41,932 --> 00:56:44,199
HE'S NOT VICIOUS.
HE'S NOT FALSE.

673
00:56:44,201 --> 00:56:46,868
YOU MAKE NOTHING
OF MY JUDGMENT, THEN !

674
00:56:46,870 --> 00:56:52,174
I-- I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.
I DON'T ASK YOU TO BELIEVE IT.
TAKE IT ON TRUST.

675
00:56:52,176 --> 00:56:56,344
BUT... WE CAN WAIT
A LONG TIME.
[ Chuckling ]

676
00:56:56,346 --> 00:56:58,447
OF COURSE.

677
00:57:00,883 --> 00:57:03,218
YOU CAN WAIT UNTIL I DIE.

678
00:57:03,220 --> 00:57:08,290
YOUR ENGAGEMENT WILL HAVE
ONE DELIGHTFUL EFFECT
ON YOU.

679
00:57:08,292 --> 00:57:11,193
IT WILL MAKE YOU
EXTREMELY IMPATIENT
FOR THAT EVENT.

680
00:57:11,195 --> 00:57:14,329
IF I DO NOT MARRY
BEFORE YOUR DEATH
I WILL NOT HAVE TO.

681
00:57:14,331 --> 00:57:17,365
THERE'S ONE THING
YOU CAN TELL HIM
IF YOU SEE HIM AGAIN.

682
00:57:17,367 --> 00:57:21,069
TELL HIM IF YOU MARRY WITHOUT
MY CONSENT, YOU'LL NOT GET
A FARTHING OF MY MONEY.

683
00:57:21,071 --> 00:57:25,340
WELL, I-I, UH--
NOT, IN THAT CASE,
TO HAVE A FARTHING OF IT.

684
00:57:29,112 --> 00:57:33,982
YOU ARE AN UNGRATEFUL,
CRUEL CHILD.

685
00:57:33,984 --> 00:57:38,353
IF YOU SEE HIM AGAIN,
YOU'LL HAVE GIVEN YOUR FATHER
THE GREATEST PAIN OF HIS LIFE.

686
00:57:40,389 --> 00:57:42,424
[ Sobbing ]

687
00:57:45,294 --> 00:57:47,329
NO !

688
00:58:38,981 --> 00:58:42,284
OH !  I'M TO TAKE IT
TO MR. TOWNSEND
AND WAIT FOR AN ANSWER.

689
00:58:42,286 --> 00:58:44,486
OH.  YEAH, I'LL
TAKE IT FOR YOU.
OH, N--

690
00:58:54,297 --> 00:58:57,833
MISS SLOPER MADE ME SWEAR
NOT TO GIVE IT TO ANYONE
BUT HIMSELF.

691
00:58:59,101 --> 00:59:02,304
SHE DID NOT INCLUDE ME
IN THAT NUMBER.
GIVE IT HERE.

692
00:59:04,106 --> 00:59:06,942
ARE YOU QUESTIONING
MY TRUSTWORTHINESS ?

693
00:59:06,944 --> 00:59:08,977
I--

694
00:59:12,348 --> 00:59:15,450
I-I WILL JUST GO ASK
THE YOUNG MISS
IF IT'S ALL RIGHT.

695
00:59:15,452 --> 00:59:18,420
YOU'LL JUST GET
MY BONNET.

696
00:59:18,422 --> 00:59:20,488
THANK YOU.

697
00:59:25,261 --> 00:59:27,362
[ Door Opening ]

698
00:59:54,290 --> 00:59:56,324
[ Sighs ]

699
00:59:59,929 --> 01:00:02,297
[ Gulps ]
HAVE YOU CALLED ME HERE
TO LOOK AT ME ?

700
01:00:11,240 --> 01:00:14,309
AS GRATIFYING
AS THAT IS,
AFTER THREE WEEKS--

701
01:00:14,311 --> 01:00:19,347
THREE WEEKS OF SILENCE,
I AM IN NEED OF
HEARING YOUR VOICE.

702
01:00:19,349 --> 01:00:23,118
I DID WANT TO LOOK AT YOU.
[ Chuckles ]

703
01:00:35,031 --> 01:00:38,566
MY FATHER HAS ASKED ME
TO GO AWAY WITH HIM...

704
01:00:38,568 --> 01:00:44,406
TO EUROPE FOR SIX MONTHS,
AND I HAVE AGREED.
HUH.

705
01:00:44,408 --> 01:00:48,310
SO, IT'S DONE.

706
01:00:48,312 --> 01:00:51,346
YOU'VE GIVEN ME UP
FOR HIM.

707
01:00:51,348 --> 01:00:56,351
NO, MORRIS.  NO.
LET ME EXPLAIN--
EX-EXPLAIN WHAT ?

708
01:00:56,353 --> 01:01:00,989
THAT I AM...
AN UNDESIRABLE MATCH
BECAUSE I AM POOR.

709
01:01:03,459 --> 01:01:07,729
OR THAT HE BELIEVES
THAT I AM A MERCENARY.

710
01:01:09,999 --> 01:01:13,501
HE TOLD ME TO TELL YOU...

711
01:01:13,503 --> 01:01:17,672
THAT IF I MARRY YOU WITHOUT
HIS CONSENT, I SHALL NOT INHERIT
A PENNY OF HIS FORTUNE.

712
01:01:17,674 --> 01:01:19,708
[ Slams Fist ]

713
01:01:19,710 --> 01:01:23,178
PLEASE TELL HIM
THAT I DON'T GIVE A DAMN
FOR HIS MESSAGE,

714
01:01:23,180 --> 01:01:27,148
AND THAT I DON'T WANT
NOR NEED HIS MONEY.

715
01:01:27,150 --> 01:01:31,252
- MARRY ME.
- WITHOUT HIS CONSENT ?

716
01:01:31,254 --> 01:01:36,057
CATHERINE...
YOU CAN'T PLEASE US BOTH.

717
01:01:36,059 --> 01:01:38,393
YOU HAVE TO CHOOSE.

718
01:01:39,328 --> 01:01:41,596
I HAVE.

719
01:01:41,598 --> 01:01:43,665
I HAVE CHOSEN YOU.

720
01:01:45,368 --> 01:01:50,005
HE IS TAKING ME TO EUROPE
TO TEST OUR DEVOTION.

721
01:01:50,007 --> 01:01:53,408
NO.  NO, HE'S
TAKING YOU TO EUROPE
SO THAT YOU'LL FORGET ME.

722
01:01:53,410 --> 01:01:55,477
NO.

723
01:01:59,348 --> 01:02:02,417
PEOPLE THINK
TERRIBLE THINGS, MORRIS.

724
01:02:04,520 --> 01:02:07,389
THEY DON'T KNOW
WHAT IS BETWEEN US.

725
01:02:08,391 --> 01:02:12,327
THEY SEE YOU,
AND THEN THEY SEE ME AND--

726
01:02:13,562 --> 01:02:15,797
FATHER DOESN'T UNDERSTAND.

727
01:02:21,504 --> 01:02:25,173
[ Sighs ]
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

728
01:02:28,477 --> 01:02:31,646
FORGIVE ME, BUT I CANNOT--

729
01:02:31,648 --> 01:02:35,450
I CANNOT FORSAKE HIM SO.

730
01:02:35,452 --> 01:02:37,552
[ Crying ]

731
01:02:43,292 --> 01:02:45,427
PLEASE... PLEASE...

732
01:02:46,595 --> 01:02:48,663
WAIT FOR ME.

733
01:02:50,266 --> 01:02:53,368
PLEASE, WAIT...

734
01:02:53,370 --> 01:02:55,336
FOR ME, MORRIS.

735
01:03:09,852 --> 01:03:12,253
[ Whispering ]
I'LL WAIT FOR YOU.
[ Relieved Sigh ]

736
01:03:12,255 --> 01:03:14,322
I'LL WAIT FOR YOU.

737
01:03:22,364 --> 01:03:24,566
BUY YOUR WEDDING GOWN
IN PARIS.

738
01:03:27,369 --> 01:03:30,738
[ Laughs, Sniffs ]
SOME-SOMETHING
BEAUTIFUL.

739
01:03:30,740 --> 01:03:33,875
SOMETHING BEAUTIFUL
THAT'S WORTHY OF YOU.

740
01:03:38,414 --> 01:03:41,182
* [ Band ]

741
01:03:41,184 --> 01:03:43,485
[ Crowd Shouting Joyfully ]

742
01:03:48,257 --> 01:03:52,427
FATHER !  FATHER !

743
01:03:52,429 --> 01:03:56,764
-  FATHER !
- MADEMOISELLE !
  [ Continues In French ]

744
01:03:58,267 --> 01:04:00,735
[ Man, French ]
VOILA !

745
01:04:06,509 --> 01:04:08,843
[ Man Continues,
  French ]

746
01:04:19,688 --> 01:04:23,291
UN, DEUX, TROI.

747
01:04:23,293 --> 01:04:25,460
[ Crowd Exclaiming ]

748
01:04:29,431 --> 01:04:31,466
[ Panting ]

749
01:04:32,801 --> 01:04:35,870
* [ Woman Singing
    In French ]

750
01:04:58,594 --> 01:05:01,529
* [ Continues ]

751
01:05:31,660 --> 01:05:33,661
* [ Ends ]

752
01:05:33,663 --> 01:05:37,432
- CATHERINE, WE OUGHT TO P--
-  [ Catherine ]  AGNES.

753
01:05:42,771 --> 01:05:45,006
PACK.

754
01:05:45,008 --> 01:05:47,642
WE'RE LEAVING FOR GENEVA.

755
01:05:54,416 --> 01:05:57,619
[ Whispering ]
AGNES... HELP ME
GET OUT OF THIS.

756
01:06:03,392 --> 01:06:06,861
"WHOM IT--"
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO.

757
01:06:06,863 --> 01:06:08,997
OH, THIS I--
THIS IS PREPOSTEROUS.

758
01:06:08,999 --> 01:06:13,768
HE'S GONE TO FAR.
HE WRITE-- EH--

759
01:06:13,770 --> 01:06:16,337
HE WRITES THEY ARE TO SPEND
ANOTHER SIX MONTHS.

760
01:06:16,339 --> 01:06:18,506
ANOTHER SIX MONTHS ?

761
01:06:19,475 --> 01:06:22,410
OH.
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN ?

762
01:06:22,412 --> 01:06:24,779
WELL, IT COULD BE
ONE OF TWO THINGS.

763
01:06:24,781 --> 01:06:27,315
WELL, NO, UH, THREE.

764
01:06:27,317 --> 01:06:29,517
WE-- NO !  I'VE JUST
THOUGHT OF ANOTHER.

765
01:06:29,519 --> 01:06:34,455
LAVINIA.
[ Sighs ]  NO, IT MUST BE THAT
SHE'S PERSUADED HIM OVER TO YOU,

766
01:06:34,457 --> 01:06:38,059
AND THEY'RE BOTH SO HAPPY
THEY'VE DECIDED NOT TO
BREAK THE JOURNEY.

767
01:06:38,061 --> 01:06:42,397
OR, OR HE PROMISED THAT
IF SHE REMAIN FAITHFUL
FOR YET ANOTHER SIX MONTHS,

768
01:06:42,399 --> 01:06:45,566
IT MUST BE LOVE
AND HE WILL GIVE
HIS BLESSING.

769
01:06:45,568 --> 01:06:50,738
OR, OR, OR IN EXCHANGE FOR
HIS CONSENT, SHE'S GIVEN HIM
ANOTHER SIX MONTHS.

770
01:06:50,740 --> 01:06:55,677
IT WOULD, AFTER ALL,
BE THE LAST TIME HE HAS
HER COMPANY SO FREELY.

771
01:06:55,679 --> 01:07:01,382
OR ?
OR... SHE HAS REFUSED
TO GIVE YOU UP,

772
01:07:01,384 --> 01:07:04,452
AND HE'S HOLDING
HER HOSTAGE--

773
01:07:04,454 --> 01:07:07,422
IN SOME
NON-ENGLISH SPEAKING,
DENSELY POPULATED NATION...

774
01:07:07,424 --> 01:07:11,326
WHICH CIVILIZATION
HAS YET TO REACH--
UNTIL SHE SEES REASON.

775
01:07:16,899 --> 01:07:20,101
OH.  NOW, THERE.

776
01:07:20,103 --> 01:07:23,104
THERE, THERE.
DON'T DESPAIR.

777
01:07:23,106 --> 01:07:25,940
COOK HAS PREPARED
YOUR FAVORITE.

778
01:07:25,942 --> 01:07:27,975
LAMB CASSOULET.

779
01:07:29,111 --> 01:07:31,079
WITH THE NEW POTATOES ?

780
01:07:31,081 --> 01:07:33,414
OF COURSE.

781
01:07:33,416 --> 01:07:38,419
BY NOW, WE KNOW NOT
TO SERVE A MEAL WITHOUT
YOUR FAVORITE POTATOES.

782
01:07:43,125 --> 01:07:46,027
[ Coachman ]
HUP !  HUP !  HUP !
[ Horses Whinny ]

783
01:07:46,029 --> 01:07:48,096
[ Coachman Continues ]

784
01:08:20,729 --> 01:08:22,764
FATHER ?

785
01:08:28,070 --> 01:08:30,138
FATHER ?

786
01:09:09,044 --> 01:09:13,815
SHOULD YOU LIKE TO BE LEFT IN
SUCH A PLACE AS THIS TO STARVE ?
[ Gasping ]

787
01:09:13,817 --> 01:09:17,084
THAT'LL BE YOUR FATE.
THAT'S HOW HE'LL LEAVE YOU.

788
01:09:17,086 --> 01:09:20,688
NO, THAT'S NOT TRUE, FATHER.
YOU SHOULDN'T SAY IT.

789
01:09:20,690 --> 01:09:23,157
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING OF
WHEN I CAME UPON YOU ?

790
01:09:23,159 --> 01:09:28,763
YOU WERE GLOWING.
YOU WERE THINKING OF HIM,
WERE YOU NOT ?

791
01:09:28,765 --> 01:09:33,801
THE STORY OF HIS
ALPINE ADVENTURE.
THAT ONE OVER THERE, I IMAGINE.

792
01:09:33,803 --> 01:09:39,807
HIS YOUNG, BEAUTIFUL TORSO
DANGLING IN MIDAIR, WITH ONLY A
ROPE BETWEEN HIM AND MORTALITY.

793
01:09:39,809 --> 01:09:43,211
WELL, WE'RE ALL YOUNG
AND BEAUTIFUL ONCE.
IT'S TRANSIENT.

794
01:09:43,213 --> 01:09:46,147
WHAT WILL YOU HAVE
WHEN THAT'S GONE ?
THAT'S HIS ONLY TALENT.

795
01:09:46,149 --> 01:09:52,487
THAT, AND HOODWINKING
DIMWITTED YOUNG LADIES
OUT OF THEIR INHERITANCES.

796
01:09:52,489 --> 01:09:58,059
I LOVE HIM,
AND WHEN WE GO HOME
I SHALL MARRY HIM.

797
01:10:00,629 --> 01:10:03,264
HE SHOULD BE
VERY THANKFUL TO ME.

798
01:10:03,266 --> 01:10:06,834
A YEAR AGO YOU WERE
RUSTIC, LIMITED.

799
01:10:06,836 --> 01:10:11,138
NOW YOUR VALUE IS TWICE
AS GREAT WITH THE KNOWLEDGE
AND TASTE YOU'VE ACQUIRED.

800
01:10:11,140 --> 01:10:15,042
WE HAVE FATTENED
THE SHEEP FOR HIM
BEFORE HE KILLS IT.

801
01:10:17,212 --> 01:10:19,213
HOW OBSCENE...

802
01:10:19,215 --> 01:10:25,253
THAT YOUR MOTHER SHOULD
GIVE HER LIFE SO YOU COULD
INHABIT SPACE ON THIS EARTH.

803
01:10:48,010 --> 01:10:51,145
OH, YOUNG MAN, WHERE IS
THE BOAT FOR MERCY ?
IT'S ALREADY DOCKED, MA'AM.

804
01:10:51,147 --> 01:10:53,314
RIGHT THERE.
MM ?  OH, THANK YOU.

805
01:10:57,185 --> 01:11:01,589
[ Austin ]  THANK YOU, OFFICER.
OH, WILL THE, UH, LUGGAGE
COME ASHORE TODAY ?

806
01:11:01,591 --> 01:11:04,058
YES, SIR.
[ Lavinia ]
CATHERINE !
THANK YOU.

807
01:11:04,060 --> 01:11:07,962
OH, MY !  YOU LOOK
SO GLORIOUS.
[ Chuckles ]

808
01:11:07,964 --> 01:11:12,266
OH... HE WANTED TO
ALLOW YOU REST AFTER
YOUR JOURNEY.  OH !

809
01:11:12,268 --> 01:11:16,170
EUROPE MUST'VE
AGREED WITH YOU, AUSTIN.
YOU LOOK ALMOST CIVIL.

810
01:11:16,172 --> 01:11:19,173
I'LL GO AND ATTEND
TO THE LUGGAGE.  MAUREEN,
YOU'RE NOT MARRIED YET ?

811
01:11:19,175 --> 01:11:21,309
[ Maureen ]
OH, DOCTOR !

812
01:11:21,311 --> 01:11:24,345
HE-HE WANTED
TO COME MEET YOU.
BUT I CONVINCED HIM...

813
01:11:24,347 --> 01:11:27,315
AUSTIN WOULD THINK HIM
PRESUMPTUOUS.

814
01:11:27,317 --> 01:11:30,318
BESIDES, HE HAD PRESSING
BUSINESS AT HIS OFFICE...

815
01:11:30,320 --> 01:11:32,787
THAT REQUIRED
HIS IMMEDIATE ATTENTION.

816
01:11:32,789 --> 01:11:37,058
OH !  IT WAS TO BE A SURPRISE,
BUT HE GAVE ME LEAVE
TO TELL YOU.

817
01:11:37,060 --> 01:11:42,063
[ Laughing ]
ISN'T WONDERFUL ?  YOUR FATHER
CAN FIND NO FAULT NOW.

818
01:11:42,065 --> 01:11:44,599
AND HE'S NOT
A SUBORDINATE, EITHER.

819
01:11:44,601 --> 01:11:49,270
HE'S A PARTNER
WITH BUSINESS CARDS
AND EVERYTHING.

820
01:11:49,272 --> 01:11:52,940
[ Giggles ]
I'VE SEEN
A GREAT DEAL OF HIM.

821
01:11:52,942 --> 01:11:56,243
WELL, HE ISN'T
EASY TO KNOW.

822
01:11:56,245 --> 01:11:59,880
I SUPPOSE YOU THINK YOU
KNOW HIM, BUT YOU DO NOT.

823
01:11:59,882 --> 01:12:02,049
WELL, NOT AS I DO.

824
01:12:02,051 --> 01:12:04,986
YOU WILL KNOW HIM
AFTER YOU'VE LIVED
WITH HIM FOR A WHILE.

825
01:12:04,988 --> 01:12:08,155
I HAVE LIVED WITH HIM,
AND I MAY SAY, HE'S FULL OF--

826
01:12:08,157 --> 01:12:11,025
OH, HE'S JUST FULL OF
REMARKABLE CHARM AND ENERGY;

827
01:12:11,027 --> 01:12:13,361
FULL OF PASSION,
AND-AND--

828
01:12:13,363 --> 01:12:16,697
WHAT IS IT ?

829
01:12:16,699 --> 01:12:19,867
HE-HE WROTE ME
OF YOUR KINDNESS.
I-I THANK YOU FOR IT.

830
01:12:19,869 --> 01:12:23,204
DID YOU FAIL TO BRING
YOUR FATHER AROUND ?

831
01:12:23,206 --> 01:12:27,108
THE PURPOSE OF MY JOURNEY
WAS NOT TO BRING FATHER AROUND,
AS YOU SAY,

832
01:12:27,110 --> 01:12:30,277
BUT RATHER, TO SPEND
SOME TIME WITH HIM
BEFORE I LEFT HIS HOUSE.

833
01:12:30,279 --> 01:12:33,347
IT IS DONE.
YOU ARE THE SAME ?  YOU-YOU
HAVE NOT SWERVED THE LINE ?

834
01:12:33,349 --> 01:12:38,686
I AM THE SAME, ONLY MORE SO.
I AM HOME TO MARRY.
WITHOUT YOUR FATHER'S CONSENT ?

835
01:12:38,688 --> 01:12:42,223
WITH OR WITHOUT IT.
IT MAKES NO DIFFERENCE.

836
01:12:42,225 --> 01:12:45,326
YOU HAVE BECOME BRAVE.
PERHAPS IT DOES MAKE
A DIFFERENCE TO MORRIS.

837
01:12:45,328 --> 01:12:47,928
[ Laughs ]

838
01:12:47,930 --> 01:12:50,698
WHY ARE YOU
SO CONTRADICTORY ?

839
01:12:50,700 --> 01:12:56,237
A-A YEAR AGO YOU
WISHED ME NOT TO WORRY
ABOUT DISPLEASING FATHER.

840
01:12:56,239 --> 01:13:00,808
NO, I THANK YOU FOR
YOUR CARE OF MORRIS,
BUT, UM, I AM HOME NOW--

841
01:13:00,810 --> 01:13:02,910
TO MARRY.

842
01:13:04,346 --> 01:13:09,116
COME, LET'S GO.
YOU KNOW HOW FATHER
DISLIKES DILLYDALLYING.

843
01:13:13,121 --> 01:13:15,189
[ Dogs Barking ]

844
01:13:21,763 --> 01:13:23,064
[ Knocking At Door ]

845
01:13:31,173 --> 01:13:33,240
[ Morris Gasps ]

846
01:13:35,811 --> 01:13:38,345
[ Whispering ]
CATHERINE, I ADORE YOU.

847
01:13:43,251 --> 01:13:45,219
[ Indistinct Thudding ]

848
01:13:49,491 --> 01:13:52,193
I HAVE BEEN MISSED.

849
01:13:52,195 --> 01:13:54,795
YOU WILL MARRY ME
TOMORROW.

850
01:14:04,206 --> 01:14:06,307
TOMORROW ?
[ Panting ]

851
01:14:06,309 --> 01:14:08,409
NEXT WEEK, THEN.

852
01:14:08,411 --> 01:14:11,946
TO MAKE ME WAIT LONGER
MAY WELL JEOPARDIZE
YOUR VIRTUE.

853
01:14:15,383 --> 01:14:17,418
[ Moans ]

854
01:14:23,258 --> 01:14:25,493
[ Breathlessly ]
YOU ARE SHAMEFUL.

855
01:14:25,495 --> 01:14:29,363
TO-TO REMOVE A MAN FROM
THE OBJECT OF HIS DESIRE
FOR A DAY IS BRUTAL.

856
01:14:29,365 --> 01:14:35,402
TO DO SO FOR A YEAR
CARRIES A PENALTY SO HIGH,
ONE SHOULD NOT INCUR IT.

857
01:14:45,347 --> 01:14:47,281
OH, MORRIS.

858
01:14:47,283 --> 01:14:50,384
MM ?
I'LL MARRY YOU
ANYTIME YOU SAY.

859
01:14:53,288 --> 01:14:55,356
[ Thud ]
HUH ?

860
01:14:55,358 --> 01:14:58,225
[ Maureen ]
UH, GOOD AFTERNOON, DR. SLOPER.
UH--  OH.

861
01:14:59,895 --> 01:15:03,063
[ Austin ]
SOMEONE IN THE PARLOR ?
UH, MISS CATHERINE...

862
01:15:03,065 --> 01:15:05,900
AND MR. TOWNSEND, SIR.

863
01:15:05,902 --> 01:15:07,968
[ Laughs ]

864
01:15:17,179 --> 01:15:20,381
OH, HOW IS YOUR FATHER,
CATHERINE ?
MY FATHER DOES NOT...

865
01:15:20,383 --> 01:15:22,917
FIGURE ANYWHERE
IN THIS EQUATION.

866
01:15:22,919 --> 01:15:25,386
HE-HE'S UNCHANGED ?
YES.

867
01:15:28,824 --> 01:15:30,991
OH, MY POOR, DEAR GIRL.

868
01:15:34,930 --> 01:15:37,131
I DON'T MIND IT NOW.

869
01:15:41,603 --> 01:15:45,873
YOU MUST LET ME
TRY HIM.
NO, MORRIS.

870
01:15:45,875 --> 01:15:49,376
HE'LL NOT BE BROUGHT 'ROUND.
YOU WILL ONLY MAKE HIM WORSE.
N-- YOU SAY THAT ONLY BECAUSE...

871
01:15:49,378 --> 01:15:51,579
I MANAGED SO BADLY
THE LAST TIME.

872
01:15:51,581 --> 01:15:54,348
YET, I'VE HAD,
I'VE HAD A YEAR
TO THINK ABOUT IT NOW.

873
01:15:54,350 --> 01:15:56,450
I HAVE NEW TACT.

874
01:15:58,186 --> 01:16:01,388
IS THAT WHAT YOU'VE BEEN
THINKING ABOUT FOR A YEAR ?

875
01:16:01,390 --> 01:16:04,191
THE IDEA
STICKS IN MY CRAW.

876
01:16:04,193 --> 01:16:06,961
I-- I-I DON'T LIKE
TO FAIL.

877
01:16:06,963 --> 01:16:09,163
WELL, HOW HAVE YOU FAILED
IF WE MARRY ?

878
01:16:09,165 --> 01:16:11,932
NO-NOT ON THE MAIN ISSUE,
OF COURSE, BUT ON
THE REST OF IT--

879
01:16:11,934 --> 01:16:15,469
MY REPUTATION,
MY RELATIONS
WITH YOUR FATHER,

880
01:16:15,471 --> 01:16:18,205
UM, MY RELATION
WITH OUR CHILDREN--

881
01:16:18,207 --> 01:16:24,111
OH... WE SHALL HAVE
ENOUGH FOR OUR CHILDREN--
ENOUGH FOR EVERYTHING.

882
01:16:25,413 --> 01:16:29,316
HMM.
BESIDES,
I BELIEVE YOU WILL SUCCEED
BRILLIANTLY IN BUSINESS.

883
01:16:29,318 --> 01:16:34,321
MM, IT ISN'T OF
THE MATERIAL COMFORT
THAT I SPEAK.

884
01:16:34,323 --> 01:16:37,024
IT'S OF MORAL COMFORT;

885
01:16:37,993 --> 01:16:41,128
OF THE INTELLECTUAL
SATISFACTION.

886
01:16:44,299 --> 01:16:46,667
I HAVE GREAT
MORAL COMFORT NOW.

887
01:16:46,669 --> 01:16:49,270
YES, OF COURSE
YOU HAVE.

888
01:16:49,272 --> 01:16:52,673
Y-YOU HAVE IT WITH ME
IS DIFFERENT.  I--

889
01:16:52,675 --> 01:16:55,976
I STAKE MY PRIDE ON
PROVING TO YOUR FATHER
THAT HE'S WRONG.

890
01:16:55,978 --> 01:17:00,347
AND-- AND NOW THAT I AM
THE HEAD OF A BUSINESS,

891
01:17:00,349 --> 01:17:03,050
I CAN DEAL WITH HIM
AS AN EQUAL.

892
01:17:03,052 --> 01:17:06,253
PLEASE, CATHERINE.
PLEASE... PLEASE,
LET ME GO AT HIM.

893
01:17:06,255 --> 01:17:08,255
NO, MORRIS.

894
01:17:10,091 --> 01:17:12,092
NO.

895
01:17:12,094 --> 01:17:14,094
I HAVE GOOD REASON.

896
01:17:17,132 --> 01:17:19,233
WHAT IS IT ?

897
01:17:24,239 --> 01:17:26,273
WHAT IS IT ?

898
01:17:30,645 --> 01:17:33,414
MY FATHER DESPISES ME.

899
01:17:33,416 --> 01:17:36,650
CATHERINE, THA--
THAT ISN'T TRUE.

900
01:17:36,652 --> 01:17:39,253
DO NOT DO THAT.

901
01:17:39,255 --> 01:17:44,692
IT IS A GREAT...
THING TO BE SEPARATED
FROM YOUR FATHER.

902
01:17:46,161 --> 01:17:48,195
ESPECIALLY WHEN--

903
01:17:51,199 --> 01:17:53,233
BUT IT IS DONE.

904
01:17:53,235 --> 01:17:55,336
TAKE IT ON FAITH.

905
01:17:55,338 --> 01:17:57,404
IT--

906
01:17:59,708 --> 01:18:02,242
WE MUST NEVER
SPEAK OF IT AGAIN.

907
01:18:13,188 --> 01:18:15,289
[ Baby Crying ]
OH, HEAVEN'S SAKES,
DON'T BOUNCE.
ARTHUR !

908
01:18:15,291 --> 01:18:17,992
MAY I HELP THERE,
PLEASE ?
GO.  TAKE A WALK IN THE PARK.

909
01:18:17,994 --> 01:18:20,427
BOTH OF YOU LOOK AS IF YOU
HAVEN'T SEEN THE LIGHT OF DAY
FOR SOME TIME !

910
01:18:20,429 --> 01:18:23,397
NO, WE HAVEN'T.
SHE'S SO FRETFUL.
PERHAPS I SHOULD STAY.

911
01:18:23,399 --> 01:18:26,333
DO BE CAREFUL, PLEASE.
BE CAREFUL TO SUPPORT
HER HEAD !  MAMA !

912
01:18:26,335 --> 01:18:30,304
I RAISED EIGHT CHILDREN.
I THINK I CAN BE TRUSTED
FOR AN HOUR.

913
01:18:30,306 --> 01:18:33,340
ONE MORE MINUTE AND I WILL
WITHDRAW MY OFFER...
[ Children Giggling ]

914
01:18:33,342 --> 01:18:36,043
[ Maid ]
AWAY WITH YOU, NOW !
TO CARE FOR ELIZABETH.

915
01:18:36,045 --> 01:18:38,412
[ Man ]
MARIAN, YOUR HAT.
WE'RE GOING.

916
01:18:39,481 --> 01:18:41,582
BYE, NOW.

917
01:18:41,584 --> 01:18:44,418
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

918
01:18:44,420 --> 01:18:47,388
MARIAN.

919
01:18:47,390 --> 01:18:50,424
[ Elizabeth ]
THE YOUNG.  NO ONE KNOWS
MORE THAN THEY DO.

920
01:18:50,426 --> 01:18:53,360
ESPECIALLY NOT
THEIR PARENTS.

921
01:18:55,296 --> 01:18:57,664
HOW IS
DEAR CATHERINE ?

922
01:18:57,666 --> 01:19:01,035
AS STUBBORN AS A MULE
AND TWICE AS STUPID.

923
01:19:02,303 --> 01:19:05,606
TRIED EVERYTHING,
BUT SHE REMAINS
STUCK LIKE GLUE.

924
01:19:05,608 --> 01:19:08,542
SHE GAINED NOTHING
FROM OUR EUROPEAN TRIP,

925
01:19:08,544 --> 01:19:12,212
EXCEPT A YEAR OLDER.
[ Chuckles ]

926
01:19:12,214 --> 01:19:16,450
I CAN BARELY SIT IN
MY OWN PARLOR ANYMORE.
HIS ESSENCE PERMEATES IT.

927
01:19:16,452 --> 01:19:21,488
I CAN FIND NO REFUGE FROM MORRIS
TOWNSEND IN MY OWN HOME, AND I
HAVE LAVINIA TO THANK FOR THAT.

928
01:19:21,490 --> 01:19:25,325
SHE IS NOT A WOMAN
TO BE LEFT ALONE.

929
01:19:25,327 --> 01:19:28,262
SHE HAS TO HAVE ENTERTAINMENT.
HE WAS AVAILABLE.

930
01:19:28,264 --> 01:19:33,267
ALL THE BETTER.
WITH LAVINIA IN THE BOAT,
YOU MAY BE ASSURED IT'LL SINK.

931
01:19:33,269 --> 01:19:35,269
HEALTHY BABY.

932
01:19:35,271 --> 01:19:39,606
LAVINIA HAS A CAPITAL WAY
OF DESTROYING ALL
SHE SETS OUT TO HELP.

933
01:19:39,608 --> 01:19:43,410
[ Chuckling ]
I BELIEVE SHE FANTASIZES...

934
01:19:43,412 --> 01:19:48,182
THAT THE ATTENTION OF
THAT ABOUNDING MALE ENERGY
IN THE FRONT ROOM IS FOR HER.

935
01:19:48,184 --> 01:19:52,352
WELL, LET'S ASSUME FOR A MOMENT
THAT YOUR THEORY IS CORRECT...

936
01:19:52,354 --> 01:19:54,421
AND HE IS MERCENARY.

937
01:19:54,423 --> 01:19:58,525
WHAT DOES IT MATTER ?
YOU'VE WORKED ALL YOUR LIFE
TO AMASS THIS FORTUNE...

938
01:19:58,527 --> 01:20:02,196
KNOWING THAT CATHERINE
WOULD BE THE ONLY ONE
TO LEAVE IT TO.

939
01:20:02,198 --> 01:20:04,298
SHOULDN'T SHE HAVE
SOME HAPPINESS WITH IT,

940
01:20:04,300 --> 01:20:07,367
EVEN IF IT DOES MEAN
SHE HAS TO BUY IT ?

941
01:20:07,369 --> 01:20:13,307
THERE IS NO EVIDENCE TO SUGGEST
THAT HE WILL NOT MAKE
A FINE HUSBAND.

942
01:20:13,309 --> 01:20:16,243
DID NOT RAISE MY DAUGHTER
TO HAVE SO LITTLE DIGNITY.

943
01:20:16,245 --> 01:20:19,746
WHAT FANTASY IS BEING SHATTERED
BY HER MARRYING THIS MAN ?

944
01:20:19,748 --> 01:20:25,119
BY YOUR OWN ACCOUNT
SHE IS DIMWITTED, UNATTRACTIVE,
WITH NO SOCIAL SKILL OR GRACE.

945
01:20:25,121 --> 01:20:27,521
WHAT DREAM DID YOU HAVE
FOR THIS PRIZE ?

946
01:20:27,523 --> 01:20:30,324
WHERE DID
MORRIS TOWNSEND
FALL DOWN ?

947
01:20:32,594 --> 01:20:35,329
[ Whispering ]
MAY I HAVE SOME CAKE ?
YES, YOU CAN.

948
01:20:35,331 --> 01:20:38,432
- WELL, AUSTIN ?
- WELL...

949
01:20:40,301 --> 01:20:45,672
I THOUGHT SHE'D END HER DAYS
AT WASHINGTON SQUARE
IN THE BEST OF COMFORT.

950
01:20:47,842 --> 01:20:53,447
OH, I SUPPOSE THAT IN SOME YEARS
TO COME, SOME MAN MIGHT
HAPPEN ALONG, AND--

951
01:20:53,449 --> 01:20:57,284
A WIDOWER, PERHAPS,
WHO WOULDN'T MIND
HOW SHE WAS TOO MUCH,

952
01:20:57,286 --> 01:21:02,456
WHO WOULD BE INTENT
TO LIVE OUT THE REMAINDER
OF HIS LIFE WITH HER.

953
01:21:04,425 --> 01:21:08,729
THE AFTERNOON SUN
LIGHTS THE WEST SECTION
OF THE PARLOR;

954
01:21:08,731 --> 01:21:11,899
CATHERINE,
HEAD BENT OVER,
EMBROIDERS...

955
01:21:11,901 --> 01:21:16,403
WHILE THE WIDOWER
SMOKES HIS COB PIPE
AND READS THE NEWSPAPER.

956
01:21:16,405 --> 01:21:20,774
WELL, DON'T YOU SEE ?  THAT'D BE
SO PERFECT FOR CATHERINE.
SHE REQUIRES SO LITTLE.

957
01:21:22,544 --> 01:21:26,780
ALL THIS TIME I THOUGHT IT
WAS BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T THINK
HE WASN'T DESERVING OF HER.

958
01:21:26,782 --> 01:21:31,285
WHAT HAVE YOU DONE ?
SHE WILL NEVER LET GO.

959
01:21:32,220 --> 01:21:34,288
* [ Piano ]

960
01:21:51,806 --> 01:21:53,807
PLEASE, DON'T STOP.

961
01:22:02,850 --> 01:22:06,220
WHEN I CAME INTO THE HALL
JUST NOW...

962
01:22:07,522 --> 01:22:10,657
I WAS REMINISCING
ABOUT ALL THE TIMES
I CAME HOME TO MY DAUGHTER,

963
01:22:10,659 --> 01:22:14,595
ALMOST KNOCKING ME DOWN
THE STEPS IN HER EAGERNESS
TO GREET ME.

964
01:22:16,898 --> 01:22:18,865
DO YOU REMEMBER ?

965
01:22:18,867 --> 01:22:22,269
I REMEMBER HOW DISTASTEFUL
YOU FOUND...

966
01:22:22,271 --> 01:22:25,472
SUCH CLUMSY DISPLAYS
OF AFFECTION.

967
01:22:26,474 --> 01:22:29,243
WHEN I HEARD YOU...

968
01:22:29,245 --> 01:22:32,913
I... THOUGHT OF
YOUR DEAR MOTHER.

969
01:22:35,450 --> 01:22:37,784
ARE YOU TO MARRY HIM ?

970
01:22:37,786 --> 01:22:39,820
YES, FATHER.

971
01:22:43,758 --> 01:22:45,692
I WOULD LIKE...

972
01:22:45,694 --> 01:22:49,730
A DEFINITE NOTICE
OF WHEN YOU SET A DATE.

973
01:22:49,732 --> 01:22:52,766
WHEN A POOR MAN IS ABOUT
TO LOSE HIS ONLY CHILD,
[ Knocking ]

974
01:22:52,768 --> 01:22:55,602
HE WOULD LIKE
AN INKLING BEFOREHAND.

975
01:22:57,605 --> 01:22:59,740
THANK YOU.

976
01:23:12,387 --> 01:23:14,621
WELL, WHEN IS IT TO BE ?

977
01:23:17,292 --> 01:23:21,328
IT OCCURS TO ME
IF I LIVE WITH YOU,
I OUGHT TO OBEY YOU.

978
01:23:21,330 --> 01:23:24,064
IF THAT'S YOUR THEORY,
IT'S CERTAINLY MINE.

979
01:23:24,066 --> 01:23:28,435
BUT IF I DON'T OBEY YOU,
I OUGHT NOT TO LIVE WITH YOU--

980
01:23:28,437 --> 01:23:33,507
TO ENJOY YOUR...
KINDNESS AND PROTECTION.

981
01:23:33,509 --> 01:23:37,644
WHAT A DISTASTEFUL IDEA.
IT MUST BE MR. TOWNSEND'S.

982
01:23:37,646 --> 01:23:41,381
NO.  IT IS MINE.

983
01:23:41,383 --> 01:23:45,018
WHY DO YOU
SPEAK TO ME THUS ?

984
01:23:45,020 --> 01:23:50,457
I'VE DONE NOTHING BUT TRY
TO PROTECT YOU FROM--
FROM ?  FROM WHAT, FATHER ?

985
01:23:52,360 --> 01:23:54,461
LOVE ?

986
01:23:54,463 --> 01:23:57,097
AFFECTION ?

987
01:23:57,099 --> 01:23:59,399
CARING ?

988
01:23:59,401 --> 01:24:01,101
RESPECT ?

989
01:24:03,404 --> 01:24:05,906
IT SEEMS YOU'VE
ALREADY DEPARTED.

990
01:24:25,493 --> 01:24:27,361
[ Relieved Laugh ]

991
01:24:33,835 --> 01:24:37,137
*

992
01:24:37,139 --> 01:24:40,907
AH, IT'S SUCH
A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

993
01:24:40,909 --> 01:24:45,512
I WAS A LITTLE WORRIED
WHEN YOU SENT FOR ME TO MEET
YOU HEAR AND NOT THE HOUSE.

994
01:24:45,514 --> 01:24:49,549
BUT NOW I SEE THE REASON.
WHAT MANNER OF MAN
DO YOU THINK I AM...

995
01:24:49,551 --> 01:24:52,085
TO COME WHERE
I AM NOT WELCOME ?

996
01:24:52,087 --> 01:24:56,022
Y-YOUR FATHER DOES NOT WANT ME
IN HIS HOUSE AND I DON'T WISH
TO BE THERE.
[ Sighs ]

997
01:24:56,024 --> 01:24:59,726
OF COURSE.  HOW--
HOW INCONSIDERATE OF ME.

998
01:24:59,728 --> 01:25:03,663
OH, LET US NOT SPEAK
OF MY FATHER TODAY.
I AM EXCEEDINGLY HAPPY.

999
01:25:03,665 --> 01:25:06,466
I'M GLAD YOU ARE HAPPY.

1000
01:25:06,468 --> 01:25:08,835
ARE YOU... NOT WELL ?

1001
01:25:11,406 --> 01:25:14,775
YOU SEEM RESTLESS
AND YOU LOOK PALE.

1002
01:25:14,777 --> 01:25:17,411
I'M AFRAID
YOU ARE OVERWORKED.
[ Scoffs ]

1003
01:25:17,413 --> 01:25:20,914
YOU OUGHTN'T TO WORK SO HARD.
WELL, I DON'T WISH
TO OWE YOU EVERYTHING.

1004
01:25:24,018 --> 01:25:28,121
I SUPPOSE YOU THINK
ALL THE EFFORT
IS ON YOUR SIDE.
NO.

1005
01:25:28,123 --> 01:25:32,426
NO, I KNOW HOW DIFFICULT
THE SITUATION HAS BEEN
FOR YOU.

1006
01:25:32,428 --> 01:25:36,196
BUT IT HAS HAD THE ADVANTAGE
OF MAKING US ONE.

1007
01:25:36,198 --> 01:25:38,832
WE WILL BEAR
THINGS TOGETHER.

1008
01:25:38,834 --> 01:25:42,102
THERE ARE SOME THINGS
WE CANNOT BEAR TOGETHER--

1009
01:25:42,104 --> 01:25:44,504
SEPARATION,
FOR INSTANCE.

1010
01:25:45,206 --> 01:25:47,507
WHY DO YOU SPEAK
OF SEPARATION ?

1011
01:25:47,509 --> 01:25:50,477
WILL YOU PROMISE
NOT TO MAKE A SCENE ?

1012
01:25:50,479 --> 01:25:54,548
A SCENE ?
DO I MAKE SCENES ?

1013
01:25:54,550 --> 01:25:57,217
I MUST GO AWAY
ON BUSINESS.

1014
01:25:57,219 --> 01:26:00,153
YOUR BUSINESS IS
WITH ME NOW, MORRIS.
YES !

1015
01:26:00,155 --> 01:26:03,089
THAT IS WHAT
THE WORLD SAYS.

1016
01:26:03,091 --> 01:26:06,860
WHERE ARE YOU GOING ?
TO NEW ORLEANS
TO BUY COTTON.

1017
01:26:06,862 --> 01:26:08,929
I'LL GO WITH YOU.

1018
01:26:08,931 --> 01:26:11,865
DO YOU REALLY THINK
THAT I WOULD TAKE YOU
TO A NEST OF YELLOW FEVER ?

1019
01:26:11,867 --> 01:26:14,768
THAT I WOULD EXPOSE YOU--
IF THERE IS YELLOW FEVER,
WHY SHOULD YOU GO ?

1020
01:26:14,770 --> 01:26:18,939
WELL, TO MAKE $6,000 !
OR WOULD YOU DENY ME
THAT SATISFACTION ?

1021
01:26:18,941 --> 01:26:21,475
IF YOU CAN GO TO
NEW ORLEANS, I CAN GO !
[ Sighs ]

1022
01:26:21,477 --> 01:26:24,578
WHY SHOULDN'T YOU CATCH
YELLOW FEVER QUITE AS
EASILY AS I ?  I'M STRONG.

1023
01:26:24,580 --> 01:26:29,716
WHEN-- WHEN WE WERE IN EUROPE,
WE WERE IN MANY UNHEALTHY PLACES
AND I NEVER CAUGHT ANYTHING.

1024
01:26:29,718 --> 01:26:33,620
WELL, WHAT WILL BE
THE USE OF $6,000
IF YOU DIE OF A FEVER ?

1025
01:26:33,622 --> 01:26:36,890
WHEN A PERSON IS GOING
TO BE MARRIED, YOU SHOULDN'T
THINK ABOUT COTTON.

1026
01:26:36,892 --> 01:26:39,759
YOU SHOULD THINK ABOUT ME.
YOU COULD GO TO NEW ORLEANS
SOME OTHER TIME.

1027
01:26:39,761 --> 01:26:42,496
THEY-THEY-THEY'LL ALWAYS
BE PLENTY OF COTTON.

1028
01:26:42,498 --> 01:26:45,165
YOU SAID YOU
WOULDN'T MAKE A SCENE.
I CALL THIS A SCENE.

1029
01:26:45,167 --> 01:26:47,634
I HAVE NEVER ASKED
ANYTHING OF YOU BEFORE.

1030
01:26:47,636 --> 01:26:51,605
OH, BECAUSE I HAVE NOTHING
TO GIVE !  THANK YOU !
I NEED NO REMINDER.

1031
01:26:53,174 --> 01:26:56,109
YOU THINK TOO MUCH
OF MONEY, MORRIS.
YOU DARE SAY THAT TO ME ?

1032
01:26:56,111 --> 01:26:58,945
I-I THINK OF MONEY BECAUSE
I MUST FIND WAYS TO KEEP YOU
IN THE COMFORT...

1033
01:26:58,947 --> 01:27:01,515
TO WHICH YOU
ARE ACCUSTOMED.

1034
01:27:01,517 --> 01:27:06,653
I CAN'T FORGET THAT
I AM THE REASON THAT
YOU ARE DISINHERITED !

1035
01:27:06,655 --> 01:27:10,590
MORRIS... ARE YOU GOING
TO LEAVE ME ?

1036
01:27:10,592 --> 01:27:13,960
YES.  YES, J--
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

1037
01:27:13,962 --> 01:27:16,229
FOR HOW LONG ?

1038
01:27:16,231 --> 01:27:18,265
D-- UNTIL YOU'RE
REASONABLE AGAIN.

1039
01:27:18,267 --> 01:27:20,967
I SHALL NEVER BE REASONABLE
AGAIN IN THAT WAY.
TRY TO BE CALMER...

1040
01:27:20,969 --> 01:27:23,236
THE NEXT TIME I COME.
IS IT TOMORROW ?

1041
01:27:23,238 --> 01:27:25,805
I DON'T KNOW !
MORRIS !  MORRIS !

1042
01:27:25,807 --> 01:27:29,042
COME TOMORROW.
I'LL BE BETTER TOMORROW.

1043
01:27:29,044 --> 01:27:33,747
I'LL SHOW YOU
HOW GOOD I CAN BE.
I WILL COME WHEN I CAN.

1044
01:27:33,749 --> 01:27:38,318
I DON'T HAVE
THE LUXURY OF SLOTH.
I WORK FOR MY LIVING.

1045
01:27:40,221 --> 01:27:44,758
[ Horse Nickers ]
[ Woman ]
COME ALONG.  DON'T DAWDLE.

1046
01:27:44,760 --> 01:27:46,826
OH !

1047
01:27:46,828 --> 01:27:50,297
MY DEAR, WHAT CATASTROPHE
HAS BEFALLEN US ?

1048
01:27:50,299 --> 01:27:53,633
WELL, TAKE MR. SHAKESPEARE'S
ADVICE: "GIVE SORROW WORDS;

1049
01:27:53,635 --> 01:27:57,337
THE GRIEF THAT DOES NOT SPEAK
WHISPERS THE O'ER-FRAUGHT HEART
AND BIDS IT BREAK."

1050
01:27:57,339 --> 01:28:00,173
I KNOW NOT OF WHAT SORROW
YOU SPEAK.

1051
01:28:00,175 --> 01:28:03,176
COME, COME, MY DEAR.
YOUR EYES ARE NOT
REDDENED WITH JOY.

1052
01:28:03,178 --> 01:28:06,846
[ Indistinct Whispering ]
YOUR PRIDE
IS MY PRIDE.

1053
01:28:06,848 --> 01:28:12,252
YOUR SUSCEP--
SUSCEPTIBILITIES ARE MY--
I SEE YOUR SIDE.

1054
01:28:12,254 --> 01:28:15,255
BUT I ALSO SEE
THE SITUATION AS A WHOLE.

1055
01:28:19,327 --> 01:28:22,162
YOUR FATHER MUST BEAR
THE BRUNT OF YOUR ANGER.

1056
01:28:23,297 --> 01:28:26,266
MORRIS DID
EVERYTHING HE COULD.

1057
01:28:26,268 --> 01:28:31,071
OH, HE WAS PATIENT.
HE ALLOWED AUSTIN
TO ABUSE HIM.

1058
01:28:31,073 --> 01:28:34,708
HOW MUCH CAN
A YOUNG MAN OF HIS TALENTS
BE EXPECTED TO TAKE ?

1059
01:28:34,710 --> 01:28:38,111
NO, CATHERINE.
WE MUST STUDY RESIGNATION.

1060
01:28:38,113 --> 01:28:41,114
RESIGNATION...
TO WHAT ?

1061
01:28:41,116 --> 01:28:44,818
- TO A CHANGE OF OUR PLANS.
- MY PLANS HAVE NOT CHANGED.

1062
01:28:46,253 --> 01:28:51,191
OH.  HE HASN'T
TOLD YOU ?
TOLD ME WHAT ?

1063
01:28:51,193 --> 01:28:54,294
WELL, WHAT HAS HAPPENED
BETWEEN YOU THEN ?

1064
01:28:54,296 --> 01:28:58,231
YOU HAVE SPOKEN
TO MR. TOWNSEND
ABOUT OUR SITUATION ?

1065
01:28:58,233 --> 01:29:00,266
[ Chuckles ]
YES !

1066
01:29:00,268 --> 01:29:03,336
I HAVE CONFERRED WITH HIM.

1067
01:29:03,338 --> 01:29:07,273
IS IT YOU, THEN,
WHO HAS CHANGED HIM
AND MADE HIM SO UNNATURAL ?

1068
01:29:08,409 --> 01:29:10,844
HE DOESN'T BELONG
TO YOU.

1069
01:29:13,214 --> 01:29:18,218
YOU HAVE NOTHING TO DO
WITH WHAT IS BETWEEN US.

1070
01:29:18,220 --> 01:29:22,222
[ Crying ]
HOW COULD YOU BE SO WICKED...

1071
01:29:23,758 --> 01:29:25,825
SO CRUEL ?

1072
01:29:25,827 --> 01:29:30,930
NO, FATHER WAS RIGHT.
YOU DO--  YOU SPOIL
EVERYTHING YOU TOUCH.

1073
01:29:30,932 --> 01:29:34,868
I WAS AFRAID OF YOU
ALL THE TIME WE WERE ABROAD.

1074
01:29:34,870 --> 01:29:38,405
I HAD NO REST WHEN THOUGHT
YOU WERE ALWAYS...
TALKING TO HIM.

1075
01:29:38,407 --> 01:29:41,975
YOU ARE A MOST
UNGRATEFUL GIRL.

1076
01:29:43,210 --> 01:29:47,080
DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO HAS LOST ?

1077
01:29:47,082 --> 01:29:49,783
I THOUGHT OF
THE YOUNG MAN
AS MY OWN--

1078
01:29:49,785 --> 01:29:52,252
[ Gasping ]
MY OWN SON.

1079
01:29:53,354 --> 01:29:59,359
I'M SURE
WE NEVER TALKED
OF ANYTHING BUT YOU.
YES.

1080
01:29:59,361 --> 01:30:05,198
YOU TALKED ABOUT ME AND TALKED
ABOUT ME UNTIL YOU MADE HIM SICK
OF THE VERY MENTION OF MY NAME.

1081
01:30:08,936 --> 01:30:12,005
IF YOU TRULY LOVED HIM...

1082
01:30:12,007 --> 01:30:14,340
YOU WOULD WANT
MORE FOR HIM.

1083
01:30:43,003 --> 01:30:45,305
[ Knocking, Creaking ]

1084
01:30:46,507 --> 01:30:51,277
- IT'S TIME ?
- CATHERINE IS DOWNSTAIRS
IN THE PARLOR.

1085
01:30:53,748 --> 01:30:55,815
[ Door Creaks, Shuts ]

1086
01:31:01,989 --> 01:31:04,924
[ Children Arguing,
 Indistinct ]

1087
01:31:06,360 --> 01:31:10,263
[ Boy #1 ]
NO, HE SAID I COULD.
[ Boy #2 ]  GET OUT OF THE WAY !

1088
01:31:10,265 --> 01:31:12,499
[ Woman ]  JAMES !
YOU SHOULD NOT
HAVE COME.

1089
01:31:12,501 --> 01:31:16,136
I'M PAST THE POINT
OF PROPRIETY.

1090
01:31:16,138 --> 01:31:20,206
I APOLOGIZE, MISS SLOPER.
I HAVE GIVEN UP
EVERYTHING FOR YOU.

1091
01:31:20,208 --> 01:31:24,244
I CAN'T BE THE CAUSE
OF YOUR LOSING
ALL THAT IS DEAR.

1092
01:31:24,246 --> 01:31:27,280
BUT ACTUALLY,
I-I HAVE NOTHING.

1093
01:31:27,282 --> 01:31:30,817
I WILL WRITE TO YOU.
THAT IS BEST.

1094
01:31:30,819 --> 01:31:33,953
I DO NOT WISH YOU
TO WRITE ME.

1095
01:31:33,955 --> 01:31:36,990
BE THE MAN
YOU PROFESS TO BE.

1096
01:31:36,992 --> 01:31:41,027
LET ME HEAR YOU SAY
YOU ARE ONLY INTERESTED
IN MY FORTUNE.

1097
01:31:41,029 --> 01:31:43,029
SAY IT...

1098
01:31:43,031 --> 01:31:45,198
SO I WILL NEVER SPEND
A SLEEPLESS NIGHT...

1099
01:31:45,200 --> 01:31:48,868
THINKING IT WAS SOMETHING
I DID OR DID NOT DO.

1100
01:31:48,870 --> 01:31:53,206
- AT LEAST GIVE ME
THAT SMALL COMFORT.
- YOUR FATHER WILL COMFORT YOU.

1101
01:31:53,208 --> 01:31:56,976
HEAVEN DELIVER ME
FROM MY FATHER'S COMFORT.

1102
01:31:56,978 --> 01:32:00,079
HE WILL REINSTATE
YOUR RIGHTS WHEN HE SEES
THAT WE'RE NOT TO MARRY.

1103
01:32:00,081 --> 01:32:02,081
SAY IT.
DON'T PUSH SO.

1104
01:32:02,083 --> 01:32:04,117
SAY IT !
[ Shouting ]
SAY WHAT ?

1105
01:32:04,119 --> 01:32:06,553
THAT-THAT I WANTED YOU
WITH YOUR MONEY ?

1106
01:32:06,555 --> 01:32:10,523
IS-IS THAT SO IMMORAL ?
[ Chuckles ]

1107
01:32:10,525 --> 01:32:14,961
WOULD YOU-- WOULD YOU WANT ME
WITHOUT MY ATTRIBUTES ?

1108
01:32:14,963 --> 01:32:18,031
YOU HAVE MONEY,
I HAVE-- I HAVE THIS.

1109
01:32:18,033 --> 01:32:20,233
IT WAS A FAIR EXCHANGE.

1110
01:32:27,208 --> 01:32:29,609
[ Door Shuts ]

1111
01:32:29,611 --> 01:32:31,911
[ Whispering ]
CATHERINE.

1112
01:32:33,347 --> 01:32:35,882
MORRIS !  MORRIS !

1113
01:32:37,351 --> 01:32:39,452
MORRIS.
[ Panting ]

1114
01:32:40,421 --> 01:32:43,456
ALL THAT IS MINE,
YOU CAN HAVE.

1115
01:32:43,458 --> 01:32:46,326
I'M INDUSTRIOUS.
I CAN COOK AND I CAN SEW.

1116
01:32:46,328 --> 01:32:48,394
I'LL LIVE SO SIMPLY.

1117
01:32:48,396 --> 01:32:51,364
[ Sighs ]

1118
01:32:51,366 --> 01:32:54,467
YOU KNOW...
10,000 A YEAR--
THAT'S A FORTUNE.

1119
01:32:54,469 --> 01:32:57,303
OH, YEAH,
BUT NOT WHEN ONE
WAS EXPECTING 30,

1120
01:32:57,305 --> 01:33:00,373
AND SPENT TWO YEARS
OF ONE'S YOUTH
IN PURSUANCE OF IT.

1121
01:33:00,375 --> 01:33:02,642
I KNOW, BUT--
I KNOW, I KNOW !

1122
01:33:02,644 --> 01:33:06,246
I KNOW WHAT I AM.
I KNOW WHAT I LACK.

1123
01:33:06,248 --> 01:33:09,148
BUT I'LL BE A LOVING,
GOOD AND UNDERSTANDING WIFE.

1124
01:33:09,150 --> 01:33:13,286
YOU'LL NEVER SUFFER
A MOMENT'S TROUBLE FROM ME.

1125
01:33:13,288 --> 01:33:17,423
MY FATHER--
I'LL GO TO MY-MY FATHER,
AND I'LL BEG HIM.

1126
01:33:17,425 --> 01:33:21,327
OH !  [ Sobbing ]
YOU CANNOT LEAVE ME
TO THAT HOUSE.

1127
01:33:21,329 --> 01:33:23,363
WHAT DO YOU WANT
ME TO DO ?

1128
01:33:23,365 --> 01:33:26,299
JUST-JUST TELL ME
WHAT YOU WANT ME TO DO.
[ Screaming ]  FOR GOD'S SAKE !

1129
01:33:26,301 --> 01:33:30,270
WHAT DO YOU THINK I AM ?
I'M NOT GOOD ENOUGH FOR YOU !

1130
01:33:30,272 --> 01:33:34,274
NOT NEARLY GOOD ENOUGH.
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO ?

1131
01:33:37,111 --> 01:33:39,245
I WANT YOU TO LOVE ME.

1132
01:33:42,650 --> 01:33:44,617
WELL, MARRY ME, THEN.

1133
01:33:45,219 --> 01:33:47,253
[ Sniffling ]

1134
01:33:48,222 --> 01:33:50,223
WHY ?

1135
01:33:58,132 --> 01:34:00,266
MORRIS !

1136
01:34:01,268 --> 01:34:03,002
[ Sobs ]
MORRIS !

1137
01:34:07,308 --> 01:34:09,409
[ Horse Whinnies ]
UUH !

1138
01:34:30,998 --> 01:34:33,032
DO YOU WANT THESE ?

1139
01:34:33,034 --> 01:34:36,336
YES.  THANK YOU, GRETA.
IT'S GINGER.

1140
01:34:36,338 --> 01:34:41,007
ARE YOU PREPARING
FOR A MARRIED LIFE
IN WHICH SERVANTS HAVE NO ROLE ?

1141
01:34:41,009 --> 01:34:44,310
THE COOK IS FRIGHTENED
OF ANYTHING NEW.

1142
01:34:44,312 --> 01:34:47,013
IF I WANT ANYTHING THAT EVEN
WHISPERS OF THE EXOTIC,
I MUST SHOW HER.

1143
01:34:47,015 --> 01:34:52,251
IT OCCURS TO  ME THAT YOU'RE
NOT... TREATING ME WITH ALL
THE CONSIDERATION I DESERVE.

1144
01:34:53,387 --> 01:34:55,421
HOW SO ?

1145
01:34:55,423 --> 01:34:58,524
WE'VE BEEN BACK FROM OUR TRIP
ALMOST THREE MONTHS.

1146
01:34:58,526 --> 01:35:02,195
YOU MUST HAVE SET
YOUR WEDDING DATE.
I ASKED THAT YOU GIVE ME NOTICE.

1147
01:35:03,397 --> 01:35:05,665
I HAVE NOT LEFT YOUR HOUSE.

1148
01:35:05,667 --> 01:35:11,304
PERHAPS NOT IN BODY,
BUT YOU MAY AS WELL BE UNDER
THE CONJUGAL ROOF...

1149
01:35:11,306 --> 01:35:14,173
FOR ALL THE BENEFIT
WE HAVE OF YOUR SOCIETY.

1150
01:35:14,175 --> 01:35:16,175
[ Catherine ]
WELL...

1151
01:35:20,681 --> 01:35:24,417
[ Clears Throat ]
I WILL TRY TO BE
MORE SOCIABLE.

1152
01:35:24,419 --> 01:35:27,086
I THINK YOU OUGHT TO.

1153
01:35:27,088 --> 01:35:30,423
YOU STRIKE ME YOU'RE
A VERY LUCKY YOUNG LADY.

1154
01:35:36,263 --> 01:35:40,700
IT WOULD BE A CONVENIENCE
TO KNOW WHEN I CAN EXPECT
AN EMPTY HOUSE.

1155
01:35:40,702 --> 01:35:45,204
FOR WHEN YOU GO,
YOUR AUNT MARCHES.

1156
01:35:45,206 --> 01:35:48,241
IS IT TOMORROW ?
NEXT WEEK ?

1157
01:35:48,243 --> 01:35:50,276
I SHALL NOT BE LEAVING.

1158
01:35:50,278 --> 01:35:53,646
HE'S BACKED OUT ?

1159
01:35:53,648 --> 01:35:57,083
I HAVE BROKEN OFF
MY ENGAGEMENT.

1160
01:35:58,819 --> 01:36:02,355
I HAVE ASKED HIM
TO LEAVE NEW YORK
FOR A LONG, LONG TIME.

1161
01:36:04,358 --> 01:36:07,393
HOW DOES HE TAKE
HIS DISMISSAL ?
I DON'T KNOW.

1162
01:36:07,395 --> 01:36:09,562
YOU MEAN YOU DON'T CARE.

1163
01:36:09,564 --> 01:36:13,232
YOU'RE VERY CRUEL,
AFTER ENCOURAGING HIM...

1164
01:36:13,234 --> 01:36:15,401
AND PLAYING HIM
FOR SO LONG.

1165
01:36:15,403 --> 01:36:17,437
I AM MY FATHER'S DAUGHTER.

1166
01:36:20,808 --> 01:36:22,842
[ Chopping ]

1167
01:36:22,844 --> 01:36:25,111
ALMOST.  TWO MORE.

1168
01:36:26,447 --> 01:36:28,514
YES, AND... VERY GOOD !

1169
01:36:28,516 --> 01:36:31,617
HAPPY BIRTHDAY !
YEA !

1170
01:36:31,619 --> 01:36:34,320
ALL RIGHT.
SIT DOWN, EVERYONE,
ON YOUR SEATS...

1171
01:36:34,322 --> 01:36:37,356
LIKE LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
NOT ANIMALS IN THE ZOO.
[ Child Giggles ]

1172
01:36:37,358 --> 01:36:41,394
PUT YOUR NAPKINS
ON YOUR CLOTHES,
PLEASE.
[ Laughing ]

1173
01:36:41,396 --> 01:36:44,297
LET ME HAVE
MY GODCHILD.
[ Boy ]
NOT ME.

1174
01:36:44,299 --> 01:36:47,834
HE IS MY DARLING.
[ Laughs ]

1175
01:36:47,836 --> 01:36:50,670
YOU HAVEN'T
EATEN ALL DAY.

1176
01:36:50,672 --> 01:36:53,739
CAN YOU BELIEVE
MY DAUGHTER IS
EIGHT YEARS OLD ?

1177
01:36:53,741 --> 01:36:57,543
DOESN'T SEEM LIKE YESTERDAY
WE WERE HERE FOR THE PURPOSE
OF MY ENGAGEMENT ?

1178
01:36:57,545 --> 01:37:00,880
[ Sighs ]
IT SEEMS VERY
LONG AGO TO ME.

1179
01:37:00,882 --> 01:37:04,317
ANOTHER LIFETIME.

1180
01:37:04,319 --> 01:37:07,420
SUPPOSE WHEN I
THINK ABOUT IT
IT DOES TO ME TOO.

1181
01:37:09,389 --> 01:37:11,891
THEY WERE GOOD DAYS,
THOUGH, CATHERINE;

1182
01:37:11,893 --> 01:37:15,428
FULL OF PROMISE,
EXPECTATION.

1183
01:37:16,363 --> 01:37:18,664
OUR WHOLE FUTURE
LAY BEFORE US.

1184
01:37:21,268 --> 01:37:23,336
CATHERINE...

1185
01:37:25,706 --> 01:37:29,275
THE COMFORT OF BEING
AN IDIOT IS THAT PEOPLE
PARDON YOU READILY.

1186
01:37:29,277 --> 01:37:32,311
- HMM.
-  FORGIVE ME.

1187
01:37:35,315 --> 01:37:38,284
DR. LUDLOW.

1188
01:37:38,286 --> 01:37:40,353
WELCOME.
GOOD EVENING,
MARIAN.

1189
01:37:40,355 --> 01:37:44,390
* AND LIGHT FAIRIES

1190
01:37:44,392 --> 01:37:46,726
* BABIES, FOXES

1191
01:37:46,728 --> 01:37:49,862
* ELVES SO MERRY

1192
01:37:49,864 --> 01:37:53,299
* COME TO SEE ME NOW

1193
01:37:53,301 --> 01:37:57,937
* THEN GO, PLEASE GO

1194
01:37:57,939 --> 01:38:01,607
* AND DANCE WITH THEM

1195
01:38:01,609 --> 01:38:05,211
* SO GO, PLEASE GO

1196
01:38:05,213 --> 01:38:08,347
* ALL NIGHT AGAIN

1197
01:38:08,349 --> 01:38:12,218
* [ Continues, Indistinct ]
IS NOT THAT
A PERFECT PICTURE ?

1198
01:38:12,220 --> 01:38:15,454
* WILL BE WAITING THERE

1199
01:38:15,456 --> 01:38:18,558
YOU KNOW,
YOU REALLY SHOULD TRY IT.

1200
01:38:19,660 --> 01:38:23,329
[ Laughs ]
WHAT ARE YOU SUGGESTING
WE TRY ?

1201
01:38:23,331 --> 01:38:28,234
MOTHERHOOD.
[ Laughing ]
WELL, MARRIAGE FIRST, OF COURSE.

1202
01:38:28,236 --> 01:38:31,204
AT LEAST, TO LEAD IN.
[ Chuckling ]

1203
01:38:31,206 --> 01:38:36,375
ALAS, IT IS NOT I
WHO POSSESS THE COLD FEET.

1204
01:38:37,911 --> 01:38:40,413
I'M GOING TO GO
AND GET SOME PORT.

1205
01:38:40,415 --> 01:38:43,316
I LEAVE MY FUTURE
IN VERY CAPABLE HANDS.

1206
01:38:43,318 --> 01:38:45,418
[ Cooing ]

1207
01:38:51,592 --> 01:38:54,393
[ Man ]  DO YOU WANT ONE ?
HE'S SO CHARMING,
CATHERINE.

1208
01:38:54,395 --> 01:38:57,563
IT SEEMS EXCEEDINGLY RUDE
TO REFUSE HIM.

1209
01:38:57,565 --> 01:39:00,800
HE'D MAKE A GOOD HUSBAND.
[ Woman Screaming ]

1210
01:39:03,303 --> 01:39:06,272
GET HELP !

1211
01:39:06,274 --> 01:39:08,608
[ Man ]
KEEP BACK.
GIVE THE MAN SOME AIR.

1212
01:39:08,610 --> 01:39:12,245
[ All Chattering ]
CATHERINE, CATHERINE !

1213
01:39:12,247 --> 01:39:14,013
[ Choking ]
CATHERINE !

1214
01:39:14,015 --> 01:39:16,282
[ Man ]
HE'S NOT BREATHING.

1215
01:39:16,284 --> 01:39:18,351
[ Crying ]

1216
01:39:31,398 --> 01:39:33,499
FATHER ?

1217
01:39:39,473 --> 01:39:43,509
WHO WOULD EVER HAVE BELIEVED
THAT DOCTORS MAKE
THE WORST PATIENTS ?

1218
01:39:43,511 --> 01:39:45,945
I WOULD.

1219
01:39:59,926 --> 01:40:01,927
YOU NEVER CHANGED THIS ROOM.

1220
01:40:01,929 --> 01:40:05,998
IN THIS ROOM,
I COULD ALLOW HER PRESENCE.

1221
01:40:11,438 --> 01:40:15,308
DO YOU SUPPOSE
YOU'LL MARRY JOHN LUDLOW ?

1222
01:40:18,345 --> 01:40:20,413
NO.

1223
01:40:21,381 --> 01:40:23,416
I DON'T SUPPOSE
I SHALL.

1224
01:40:24,985 --> 01:40:30,056
IS IT, BY CHANCE, BECAUSE
YOU PLAN TO MARRY TOWNSEND
AFTER MY DEATH ?

1225
01:40:35,662 --> 01:40:38,864
I WILL NOT LISTEN
TO TALK OF DEATH.
I'M DYING.

1226
01:40:39,800 --> 01:40:41,834
THERE'S NOTHIN'
TO TALK ABOUT.

1227
01:40:41,836 --> 01:40:44,870
AS A PHYSICIAN,
I UNDERSTAND THESE THINGS.

1228
01:40:49,843 --> 01:40:51,844
IT WOULD GIVE ME
GREAT SATISFACTION...

1229
01:40:51,846 --> 01:40:56,582
IF YOU WERE TO PROMISE
THAT UPON MY DEATH
YOU WILL NOT MARRY TOWNSEND.

1230
01:40:57,684 --> 01:41:01,387
I VERY SELDOM THINK
OF MR. TOWNSEND.

1231
01:41:01,389 --> 01:41:04,423
ALL THE EASIER
TO KEEP YOUR PROMISE.

1232
01:41:05,692 --> 01:41:07,760
I CAN'T PROMISE.

1233
01:41:09,096 --> 01:41:11,397
YOU'RE VERY OBSTINATE.

1234
01:41:13,133 --> 01:41:16,535
I DON'T THINK YOU UNDERSTAND.

1235
01:41:16,537 --> 01:41:18,537
PLEASE EXPLAIN, THEN.

1236
01:41:21,074 --> 01:41:23,142
I CAN'T EXPLAIN.

1237
01:41:24,111 --> 01:41:26,412
AND I CAN'T PROMISE.

1238
01:41:56,143 --> 01:42:00,446
THE WILL OF RECORD DIVIDED
DR. SLOPER'S ESTATE IN SIX WAYS.

1239
01:42:00,448 --> 01:42:04,183
MRS. PENNIMAN IS TO RECEIVE
$2,000 A YEAR
FOR THE REST OF HER LIFE.

1240
01:42:04,185 --> 01:42:06,419
AND MRS. ALMOND,
THE SAME AMOUNT.

1241
01:42:06,421 --> 01:42:08,988
TO HIS COUSINS,
BETHANN AND ROBERT LAWSON,

1242
01:42:08,990 --> 01:42:11,857
HE'S LEFT
A ONE-TIME GIFT OF $500.

1243
01:42:11,859 --> 01:42:15,428
MAUREEN O'DONNELL
IS TO RECEIVE...

1244
01:42:15,430 --> 01:42:17,463
$100 A YEAR
IN ADDITION TO HER SALARY...

1245
01:42:17,465 --> 01:42:21,600
AS LONG AS SHE REMAINS
AN EMPLOYEE
AT 21 WASHINGTON SQUARE.

1246
01:42:21,602 --> 01:42:25,171
CATHERINE SLOPER IS TO RECEIVE
THE BALANCE OF THE ESTATE,

1247
01:42:25,173 --> 01:42:28,941
VALUED SOMEWHERE
UPWARDS OF $300,000.

1248
01:42:30,944 --> 01:42:34,613
AS I'VE SAID,
THAT IS THE WILL OF RECORD,

1249
01:42:34,615 --> 01:42:37,483
WRITTEN SOME TEN YEARS AGO.

1250
01:42:37,485 --> 01:42:40,719
HOWEVER, SEVERAL WEEKS
BEFORE HIS DEATH,

1251
01:42:40,721 --> 01:42:42,955
THE DOCTOR
RECORDED THE CODICIL.

1252
01:42:42,957 --> 01:42:45,458
"THE AMOUNTS
ACCORDED TO ALL...

1253
01:42:45,460 --> 01:42:48,227
"REMAIN UNCHANGED
WITH ONE EXCEPTION:

1254
01:42:48,229 --> 01:42:50,663
"IN THE CASE
OF CATHERINE SLOPER,

1255
01:42:50,665 --> 01:42:55,134
"HER PORTION
HAS BEEN REDUCED TO THIS HOUSE
ON WASHINGTON SQUARE.

1256
01:42:55,136 --> 01:42:59,171
THE BULK OF THE ESTATE GOES
TO VARIOUS AND SUNDRY MEDICAL
INSTITUTIONS AROUND THE CITY."

1257
01:42:59,173 --> 01:43:01,240
HE WROTE AN EXPLANATION
OF THIS CHANGE,

1258
01:43:01,242 --> 01:43:04,210
WHICH, I'M SURE, YOU'LL WISH
TO READ IN PRIVATE, MISS SLOPER.

1259
01:43:04,212 --> 01:43:08,013
PLEASE, READ THE CODICIL,
MR. WEBBER.

1260
01:43:08,015 --> 01:43:11,617
THIS IS SOMETHING BETWEEN YOU
AND YOUR FATHER, MISS SLOPER.

1261
01:43:14,054 --> 01:43:16,255
WOULD YOU PLEASE EXCUSE US ?

1262
01:43:16,257 --> 01:43:18,724
NO.
WE HAVE SOME FAMILY MATTERS
TO ATTEND TO.

1263
01:43:18,726 --> 01:43:21,560
BY THE VERY NATURE
OF THE GESTURE...

1264
01:43:22,262 --> 01:43:24,530
AND THE FACT--

1265
01:43:25,265 --> 01:43:28,033
PLEASE, EVERYONE, SIT.

1266
01:43:29,169 --> 01:43:31,871
AND PLEASE READ IT TO ME,
MR. WEBBER.

1267
01:43:36,076 --> 01:43:39,678
"SHE IS AMPLY PROVIDED FOR
ON HER MOTHER'S SIDE,

1268
01:43:39,680 --> 01:43:44,049
"NEVER HAVING SPENT MORE THAN
A FRACTION OF HER INCOME
FROM THIS SOURCE.

1269
01:43:44,051 --> 01:43:47,186
"SO THAT HER FORTUNE
IS ALREADY MORE THAN SUFFICIENT
TO ATTRACT...

1270
01:43:47,188 --> 01:43:51,123
"THE UNSCRUPULOUS ADVENTURERS
WHO SHE HAS GIVEN ME
REASON TO BELIEVE...

1271
01:43:51,125 --> 01:43:54,727
THAT SHE PERSISTS IN REGARDING
AS AN INTERESTING CLASS."

1272
01:43:54,729 --> 01:43:58,197
- YOU MUST BREAK THE WILL.
-  NO, NO, NO.  I--
 [ Giggles ]

1273
01:43:58,199 --> 01:44:01,300
I LIKE IT VERY MUCH.

1274
01:44:01,302 --> 01:44:05,638
CATHERINE, IT'S--
IT'S A TRAVESTY.
NO, NO.

1275
01:44:05,640 --> 01:44:07,740
I THINK, UM,
IT'S RATHER FLATTERING.

1276
01:44:07,742 --> 01:44:11,544
I THINK IT'S THE PERFECTLY
FITTING CONCLUSION...

1277
01:44:11,546 --> 01:44:16,282
TO THE SAGA OF FATHER'S
ALL-IMPORTANT FORTUNE.

1278
01:44:17,751 --> 01:44:20,920
I LIKE IT...
VERY MUCH, INDEED.

1279
01:44:22,022 --> 01:44:26,225
LET'S HAVE, UM,
SOME TEA, SHALL WE ?

1280
01:44:26,227 --> 01:44:29,295
OH, NO, NO.
PERHAPS SOMETHING STRONGER.

1281
01:44:29,297 --> 01:44:32,298
AUNT LAVINIA, LET'S
BREAK OUT THE GOOD PORT.

1282
01:44:32,300 --> 01:44:35,167
WELL, IS IT NOT
CUSTOMARY TO CELEBRATE
THE READING OF THE WILL ?

1283
01:44:35,169 --> 01:44:37,836
[ Giggling ]

1284
01:44:37,838 --> 01:44:40,205
COME ON, EVERYONE.
JOIN ME, PLEASE.

1285
01:44:40,207 --> 01:44:43,809
[ Giggling ]

1286
01:44:43,811 --> 01:44:48,147
* THERE ONCE WAS A PLAIN
 LITTLE PIECE OF STRING *

1287
01:44:48,149 --> 01:44:52,818
* ALL ALONE
AND WITH NOTHING TO DO *

1288
01:44:52,820 --> 01:44:57,256
* EACH NIGHT IT WOULD WISH
MORE THAN ANYTHING *

1289
01:44:57,258 --> 01:45:01,794
* FOR A SOMEONE
TO TIE ITSELF TO *

1290
01:45:01,796 --> 01:45:06,332
* THEN ONE DAY A FINGER
 CAME WANDERING BY *

1291
01:45:06,334 --> 01:45:10,936
* AND THE PLAIN LITTLE STRING
 QUICKLY CAUGHT HIS EYE *

1292
01:45:10,938 --> 01:45:15,174
* THE FINGER SAID
 JUST COME ALONG WITH ME

1293
01:45:15,176 --> 01:45:19,378
* I CAN TELL YOU
 HOW HAPPY YOU'LL BE *

1294
01:45:19,380 --> 01:45:24,650
* I HAVE A BROKEN STRING
 ON MY FIDDLE

1295
01:45:24,652 --> 01:45:28,153
* I CANNOT PLAY A THING
ON MY FIDDLE *

1296
01:45:28,155 --> 01:45:32,625
* AND MUSICALLY SPEAKING
YOU'RE JUST WHAT I'M SEEKING *

1297
01:45:32,627 --> 01:45:36,895
* WITH YOU
I'LL BE ABLE TO PLAY *

1298
01:45:36,897 --> 01:45:41,000
* YOU'VE MADE A MISTAKE
SAID THE LITTLE STRING *

1299
01:45:41,002 --> 01:45:45,337
* I HAVE NEVER
MADE MUSIC BEFORE *

1300
01:45:45,339 --> 01:45:49,908
* THE FINGER SAID
I'LL TEACH YOU HOW TO SING *

1301
01:45:49,910 --> 01:45:54,146
* AND YOU WON'T
BE ALONE ANYMORE *

1302
01:45:54,148 --> 01:45:58,283
* HE PLAYED ON THE STRING
AT A FANCY DRESS BALL *

1303
01:45:58,285 --> 01:46:02,788
* AND THE SOUND
THRILLED THE DANCERS
AND FILLED THE HALL *

1304
01:46:02,790 --> 01:46:06,725
* SO SOMETIMES A PLAIN
LITTLE PIECE OF STRING *

1305
01:46:06,727 --> 01:46:11,296
* MAKES THE PRETTIEST MUSIC
OF ALL *

1306
01:46:12,432 --> 01:46:16,168
-  GOING-HOME TIME.
- [ All ]
  AWW !

1307
01:46:16,170 --> 01:46:19,772
WELL, IT MUST BE
NO ONE WANTS THE BISCUITS
THAT GRANDMA'S BAKED.

1308
01:46:19,774 --> 01:46:22,341
[ All Chattering ]

1309
01:46:24,144 --> 01:46:27,146
EDITH, IS YOUR MOTHER
WORKING LATE AGAIN TONIGHT ?
MM-HMM.

1310
01:46:27,148 --> 01:46:29,114
[ Girl ]
WAIT FOR ME !

1311
01:46:29,116 --> 01:46:31,750
WELL, YOU MUST HELP ME
CLEAN UP THIS MESS !

1312
01:46:35,021 --> 01:46:38,090
I NEVER CAN SEEM
TO MANAGE IT ALONE.

1313
01:46:38,092 --> 01:46:40,459
THERE'S ALWAYS
SO MUCH TO DO.

1314
01:46:42,328 --> 01:46:45,931
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT THERE ?
MY BOOK.

1315
01:46:45,933 --> 01:46:47,966
WHAT IS THAT ?

1316
01:46:50,303 --> 01:46:52,905
WHAT'S THAT SAY ?
"UPS--"

1317
01:46:52,907 --> 01:46:56,308
UPSETTING.
[ Murmuring ]

1318
01:46:56,310 --> 01:47:02,247
- THAT'S RIGHT.
"PONDO, THE DOG, WHO WAS--"
- [ Gasps ]

1319
01:47:02,249 --> 01:47:06,018
OH, MY DEAR !
OH, MY DEAR, THIS WILL NOT DO !

1320
01:47:06,020 --> 01:47:09,722
IT WILL NOT DO AT ALL.
[ Gasping ]
WHAT ?  AUNT ?

1321
01:47:09,724 --> 01:47:12,991
YOU KNOW, THE MOST-- THE MOST
EXTRAORDINARY HAPPENSTANCE.
[ Laughing ]

1322
01:47:12,993 --> 01:47:15,060
OH, I HAD THE GOOD--
NOW PROMISE ME--

1323
01:47:15,062 --> 01:47:17,262
OH, PROMISE ME--
PROMISE ME YOU'LL BE CIVIL.

1324
01:47:17,264 --> 01:47:19,298
PROMISE ME, CATHERINE.

1325
01:47:19,300 --> 01:47:21,333
PROMISE ME.

1326
01:47:23,103 --> 01:47:25,170
THANK YOU.

1327
01:47:35,248 --> 01:47:38,283
AUNT, UM, COULD YOU TAKE EDITH
IN FOR SOME MILK AND BISCUITS ?

1328
01:47:38,285 --> 01:47:41,320
OH, YES.  COME ALONG NOW.

1329
01:47:41,322 --> 01:47:43,856
WHAT'S YOUR NAME ?
EDNA ?
EDITH.

1330
01:47:43,858 --> 01:47:46,325
COME ON.

1331
01:47:49,229 --> 01:47:51,430
[ Sighs ]

1332
01:47:58,838 --> 01:48:00,973
THERE HAVE BEEN CHANGES.

1333
01:48:02,909 --> 01:48:04,977
HMM.

1334
01:48:11,384 --> 01:48:14,486
HOW HAVE THE YEARS
TREATED YOU, MORRIS ?
BADLY.

1335
01:48:14,488 --> 01:48:17,356
BUT, UM--
[ Crockery Clatters ]

1336
01:48:17,358 --> 01:48:21,426
I SUPPOSE YOU WOULD SAY
THAT'S AS IT SHOULD HAVE BEEN.

1337
01:48:27,367 --> 01:48:29,234
YOU LOOK VERY WELL.

1338
01:48:32,172 --> 01:48:34,339
I HAVE--

1339
01:48:34,341 --> 01:48:37,242
I HAVE VENTURED--

1340
01:48:37,244 --> 01:48:40,279
I SO MUCH WANTED TO--

1341
01:48:42,515 --> 01:48:46,385
I WAS DETERMINED THAT--
WILL YOU NOT SIT DOWN ?

1342
01:48:46,387 --> 01:48:49,388
NO, I THINK
I HAD BETTER NOT.

1343
01:48:55,962 --> 01:48:58,030
FOR MANY YEARS
IT HAS BEEN...

1344
01:48:58,032 --> 01:49:02,234
MY DEEPEST DESIRE
TO BE FRIENDS AGAIN.

1345
01:49:04,103 --> 01:49:06,271
WELL, WE BOTH KNOW
WE WERE NEVER FRIENDS.

1346
01:49:06,273 --> 01:49:09,241
OH, CATHERINE,
YOU DO ME AN INJUSTICE.

1347
01:49:12,111 --> 01:49:14,079
YOU TREATED ME BADLY.

1348
01:49:14,081 --> 01:49:17,216
NOT IF YOU
THINK OF IT RIGHTLY.

1349
01:49:17,218 --> 01:49:19,251
YOU HAD YOUR LIFE
WITH YOUR FATHER,

1350
01:49:19,253 --> 01:49:22,888
WHICH WAS WHAT I COULDN'T
MAKE UP MY MIND TO ROB YOU OF.

1351
01:49:22,890 --> 01:49:24,923
YES.  I HAD THAT.

1352
01:49:26,993 --> 01:49:30,295
THE PAST CAN BE PUT BEHIND US
IF YOU WILL ALLOW IT.

1353
01:49:30,297 --> 01:49:32,264
I WILL NOT ALLOW IT.

1354
01:49:32,266 --> 01:49:35,200
YOU HURT ME TOO BADLY.

1355
01:49:36,936 --> 01:49:39,271
I FELT IT VERY MUCH.

1356
01:49:39,273 --> 01:49:41,340
I FELT IT FOR YEARS.

1357
01:49:42,308 --> 01:49:45,310
IT MADE A GREAT CHANGE
IN MY LIFE.

1358
01:49:48,114 --> 01:49:50,449
BUT I CAN'T
TALK ABOUT IT.

1359
01:49:56,356 --> 01:49:58,590
WHY DIDN'T YOU
MARRY, THEN ?

1360
01:49:58,592 --> 01:50:01,293
LAVINIA TELLS ME...

1361
01:50:01,295 --> 01:50:03,362
THERE HAVE BEEN CHANCES.

1362
01:50:03,364 --> 01:50:05,631
I DIDN'T WISH TO MARRY.

1363
01:50:05,633 --> 01:50:07,666
YES.

1364
01:50:09,469 --> 01:50:11,503
YOU HAD NOTHING TO GAIN.

1365
01:50:11,505 --> 01:50:13,572
I HAD NOTHING TO GAIN.

1366
01:50:19,112 --> 01:50:21,580
WHAT EVER ELSE HAPPENED,
I DID--

1367
01:50:21,582 --> 01:50:23,649
I DID LOVE ONCE.

1368
01:50:25,318 --> 01:50:28,353
WELL, ACTUALLY.

1369
01:50:31,391 --> 01:50:33,425
DO YOU HATE ME ?

1370
01:50:33,427 --> 01:50:35,494
NO.

1371
01:50:36,429 --> 01:50:39,498
BUT PLEASE
DON'T COME HERE AGAIN.

1372
01:50:46,439 --> 01:50:49,041
GOOD-BYE, THEN.

1373
01:51:12,398 --> 01:51:15,267
* [ Piano ]

1374
